Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.37,0:00:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Our convention program contains
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.37,0:00:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,over 100 audio and video productions,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.12,0:00:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,including the one we just enjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.79,0:00:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,These videos are made\Nat various locations around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.67,0:00:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the privilege of supporting this
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.47,0:00:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and other aspects of the Kingdom work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.35,0:00:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,For your convenience,\Ndonations can be made online
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.56,0:00:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,at donate.jw.org.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.81,0:00:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As we saw,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.82,0:00:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the prophet Daniel maintained his faith
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.24,0:00:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,despite tests and infirmities.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.32,0:00:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we do the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.12,0:00:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What strength can we gain\Nfrom the prophetic visions given to Daniel?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.66,0:01:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Please pay close attention
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.66,0:01:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to Brother Stephen Lett of the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.25,0:01:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as he answers those questions\Nin the final talk
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.84,0:01:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of this convention, entitled 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.30,0:01:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“Become Powerful by Your Faith!”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.10,0:01:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A building constructed\Nwith steel-reinforced concrete
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.56,0:01:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,can withstand powerful earthquakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.73,0:01:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A tree with strong, deep roots
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.11,0:01:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,can remain standing\Nin the face of many powerful storms.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.03,0:01:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,An athlete made powerful by rigorous training
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.58,0:01:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,can successfully complete a decathlon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.25,0:01:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,—a ten-event athletic contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.25,0:01:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, just as a building, a tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.22,0:01:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and an athlete can be powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.55,0:01:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we as Jehovah’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.93,0:02:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,can be powerful by means of our faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.77,0:02:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will discuss during this talk\Nhow faith
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.19,0:02:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,—a product of holy spirit,\Nthe most powerful force in the universe—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.11,0:02:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,can reinforce, or fortify, us
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.19,0:02:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for any (and I mean any)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.16,0:02:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,test, trial, or temptation
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.49,0:02:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, even though\Nwe may not feel powerful physically
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.21,0:02:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or emotionally,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.29,0:02:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,our faith can make us powerful spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.96,0:02:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And spiritual power is much more valuable
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.26,0:02:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,than physical or emotional power.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.97,0:02:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,With spiritual power, we can be like Abraham.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.47,0:02:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Please go to Romans chapter 4,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.31,0:02:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and notice what was said about Abraham,\Nbeginning in verse number 18:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.07,0:02:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“Although beyond hope, yet based on hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“he had faith that he would become\Nthe father of many nations
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.78,0:03:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“according to what had been said:\N‘So your offspring will be.’
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.71,0:03:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“And although he did not grow weak in faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.42,0:03:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“he considered his own body,\Nnow as good as dead
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.59,0:03:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“(since he was about 100 years old),
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.96,0:03:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“as well as the deadness\Nof the womb of Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.97,0:03:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“But because of the promise of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.93,0:03:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“he did not waver in a lack of faith;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.89,0:03:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“but he [now notice]
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.02,0:03:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“became powerful by his faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.48,0:03:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“giving God glory and being fully convinced
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.57,0:03:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“that what He [Jehovah] had promised
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.90,0:03:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He [Jehovah] was also able to do.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.45,0:03:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though almost 100 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.41,0:03:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,—and Abraham likely\Nwould have been frail physically
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.04,0:03:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and emotionally weak at times—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.42,0:03:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,his faith made him powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.38,0:03:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, his faith made him so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.80,0:04:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that he believed this extraordinary promise\Nwith all his heart
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.81,0:04:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,—that his almost 90-year-old wife, Sarah,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.14,0:04:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,would give birth to a son\Nand that it would definitely come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.77,0:04:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And even though that promise\Nwas unbelievable from a human standpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.78,0:04:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he had no doubt whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.11,0:04:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, likewise, if our faith\Nmakes us powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.45,0:04:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we will fully believe\Nall of Jehovah’s promises
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.62,0:04:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter how extraordinary they may seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.50,0:04:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We will do so without doubting whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.92,0:04:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But now think about this comparison\Nto Abraham:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.72,0:04:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,An older, frail,\Nchronically ill servant of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.47,0:04:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,may seem weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.64,0:04:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but outward appearance can be very deceptive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.48,0:04:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If that one has been empowered by faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.94,0:04:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,then he is truly strong, just like Abraham.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.28,0:05:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And this wonderful convention
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.61,0:05:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,was designed to fortify our faith
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.66,0:05:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it will empower us to be so strong
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.58,0:05:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’ll be able to endure\Nwhatever test, trial, and temptation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.00,0:05:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,comes against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.09,0:05:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And there will actually be no breaking point
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.71,0:05:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to our integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.76,0:05:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But now let’s talk about how each day\Nof our convention
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.76,0:05:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and our outstanding drama
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.18,0:05:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,have strengthened our faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.98,0:05:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let’s talk about Friday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.35,0:05:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The day’s theme was a quote from Luke 17:5:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.36,0:05:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“Give us more faith.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.28,0:05:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these were the humble words\Nof Jesus’ apostles
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.62,0:05:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,who recognized their need for more faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.16,0:05:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were humbly pleading for such.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.29,0:05:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we feel the same way, don’t we?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.37,0:05:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We know we need more faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.83,0:05:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and we humbly ask Jehovah for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.92,0:06:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But now the question is,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.92,0:06:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Will Jehovah answer our pleas for more faith?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.64,0:06:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he will.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.30,0:06:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And Friday revealed\Nsome of the ways Jehovah answers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.68,0:06:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,our humble plea for more faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.10,0:06:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As illuminated on Friday,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.61,0:06:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gives us faith
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.82,0:06:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,primarily by means of two books
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.99,0:06:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—the Bible and the book of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.99,0:06:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The first symposium showed\Nhow the Bible builds faith
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.00,0:06:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in God’s existence;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.46,0:06:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it builds faith in itself,\Nthat it’s the Word of God;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.83,0:06:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it builds faith in God’s moral standards;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.92,0:06:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and it builds faith in God’s love for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.05,0:06:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we ask that first part,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.05,0:06:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How does the Bible build faith\Nin God’s existence?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.56,0:06:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for one thing, within its pages,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.06,0:06:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it gives us common sense,\Nreasoning from scriptures
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.65,0:06:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,such as Hebrews 3:4.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.94,0:07:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And do you know what that says?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.94,0:07:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “Of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.36,0:07:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“every house is constructed by someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.66,0:07:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but the one\Nwho constructed all things is God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.58,0:07:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you could never convince\Nany sane person
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.29,0:07:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that a beautiful house\Ndesigned and built itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.29,0:07:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even more so,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.38,0:07:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it should not be possible\Nto convince any rational person
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.55,0:07:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that all the beautiful creations around us
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.39,0:07:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,just designed and built themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.06,0:07:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,or that they’re the product of blind chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.85,0:07:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Where there is design,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.02,0:07:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,there is always a designer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.90,0:07:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s illustrate this:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.03,0:07:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.03,0:07:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,would you have to throw\Nblack paint from a can
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.16,0:07:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,onto a white ceiling
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.45,0:07:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,until you produced
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.50,0:07:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a perfect map of New York City,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.96,0:08:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,until the paint particles scattered\Naccurately identifying all of the streets,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.96,0:08:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the highways, the tunnels, the bridges,\Nthe overpasses, and the landmarks
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.51,0:08:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and correctly named each one?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.22,0:08:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you could do that\Nfor billions of times,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.22,0:08:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and never would you produce\Na perfect map of New York City.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.27,0:08:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now to add a little humor:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.27,0:08:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s say you tried doing this\Nfor 100 billion years, and you get excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.23,0:08:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You finally got a city map.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.24,0:08:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But, oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.24,0:08:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not New York City;\Nit’s Warwick, New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.66,0:08:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you’ve got to start all over,\Ngoing for that map of New York City.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.54,0:08:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to give you a little humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.83,0:08:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But think of this: One living human cell
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.13,0:08:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is much more complex,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.26,0:08:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,intricately designed,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.34,0:08:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,than a map of New York City.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.34,0:08:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And one human body
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.68,0:08:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is made up of about 100 trillion\Nof such amazing cells
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.97,0:09:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all working together harmoniously.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.69,0:09:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in the second part,\Nhow does the Bible build faith in itself
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.48,0:09:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,—that it is the Word of God?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.78,0:09:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for one thing,\Neverything the Bible recommends
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.03,0:09:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,works and brings superior results
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.41,0:09:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,—how to raise children,\Nhow to have a happy marriage, and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.71,0:09:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it:\NHumans simply aren’t smart enough
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.79,0:09:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to recommend only what works,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.05,0:09:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and their advice is constantly being revised\Nand updated, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.05,0:09:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Though written hundreds,\Nthousands, of years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.43,0:09:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible has never needed to be revised.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.18,0:09:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, everything it recommends works.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.98,0:09:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to be from a higher source\Nthan humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.77,0:09:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in the third part, how does the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.48,0:09:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,build faith in God’s moral standards?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.36,0:09:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it tells us what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.57,0:09:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It encourages us to obey them,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.24,0:09:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.24,0:10:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it protects us physically,\Nemotionally, and spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.04,0:10:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We get happiness;\Nwe get a good conscience;
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.50,0:10:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we experience the benefits.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.96,0:10:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, we don’t have to learn\Nthe painful process
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.55,0:10:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of trial and error.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.55,0:10:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a saying\Nthat “experience is the best teacher”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.10,0:10:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,—completely wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.14,0:10:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Experience is a school of hard knocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.10,0:10:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is the best Teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.48,0:10:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah is . . . making\Nthe inexperienced one wise,”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.32,0:10:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,according to Psalm 19:7.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.78,0:10:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in the fourth part, how does the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.45,0:10:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,build faith in God’s love for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.20,0:10:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The most powerful way is,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.21,0:10:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it explains how Jehovah gave\Nhis firstborn Son to die for us
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.21,0:10:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we could have everlasting life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.96,0:10:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now think about it:\NWhat do most people give away
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.30,0:10:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,if they give something away?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.34,0:11:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Something they don’t need\Nor at least something they can do without.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.51,0:11:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah gave at great cost,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.60,0:11:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,great pain to himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.27,0:11:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution teaches
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.40,0:11:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that our ancestors were apes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.23,0:11:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How could we feel happy and feel loved
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.53,0:11:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking that an ape was our father?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.45,0:11:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But our real Father, Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.91,0:11:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is the personification of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.58,0:11:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, on Friday afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.96,0:11:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we had our second symposium,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.30,0:11:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,which opened the book of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.38,0:11:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And peering into this book
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.01,0:11:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,can empower our faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.43,0:11:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let’s talk about that first talk\Nthat dealt with the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.39,0:11:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 40:26 tells us
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.11,0:11:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah created all of them
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.99,0:11:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and ‘he calls all of them by name.’
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.99,0:12:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s ponder this for a moment:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.37,0:12:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How long would it take you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.74,0:12:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to name just the stars\Nin the Milky Way galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.25,0:12:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,if you named one every second?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.83,0:12:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph, Paul, Rachel, Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.71,0:12:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, scientists estimate
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.05,0:12:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that there are perhaps 400 billion stars
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.72,0:12:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,just in the Milky Way galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.72,0:12:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you named one a second,\Nit would take you 400 billion seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.64,0:12:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how long is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.48,0:12:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Twelve thousand six hundred\Nand eighty four years
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.11,0:12:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,—more than twice the time that has passed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.78,0:12:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,since the creation of Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.57,0:12:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you could go to the next galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.91,0:12:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And scientists estimate
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.03,0:12:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that there may be two trillion galaxies\Nin the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.83,0:12:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s five times the number of galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.42,0:12:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as our individual stars in the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.88,0:13:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you ponder that,\Nit will really give you a headache.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.76,0:13:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, Jehovah created, sustains,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.97,0:13:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and calls every one of them by name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.06,0:13:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And the talk made the point\Nthat if Jehovah can do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.56,0:13:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,he will have no problem\Nremembering and recreating
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.52,0:13:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,all those sleeping in the memorial tombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.19,0:13:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The second talk examined\Nthe page in the book of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.82,0:13:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,about the oceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.07,0:13:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How powerful they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But the One who made them\Nis vastly more powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.83,0:13:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And our powerful God\Ndefinitely can protect us now
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.84,0:13:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and right through the great tribulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.71,0:13:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The third talk examined\Nthe page in creation about the forests,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.39,0:13:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was discussed how forests\Nhave the amazing ability
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.31,0:13:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to repair and renew themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.44,0:13:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And the point was made that the One\Nwho has the wisdom to create such forests
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.44,0:14:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,surely knows how to undo all the damage
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.82,0:14:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that man has done to the planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.66,0:14:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The fourth talk focused on wind and water,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.12,0:14:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and it talked about how Jehovah\Nhas in the past used wind and water
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.67,0:14:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,—and especially water in the form of hail—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.75,0:14:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to defeat his enemies and deliver his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.67,0:14:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he will use them again at Armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.01,0:14:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The fifth talk took a glimpse
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.47,0:14:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,into the fascinating world of sea creatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.81,0:14:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and we looked at the largest animal alive\Non earth today
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.35,0:14:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,—the blue whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.36,0:14:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And what an appetite
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.36,0:14:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that blue whale has!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.74,0:14:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It can eat, according to the video,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.16,0:14:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,tons of food every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.41,0:14:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, Jehovah feeds it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.49,0:14:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if he can do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.66,0:14:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,can he not feed and care for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.67,0:15:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if we continue to seek first the Kingdom?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.17,0:15:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, our faith was strengthened
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.26,0:15:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that he can and he will.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.43,0:15:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The last talk examined our amazing bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.39,0:15:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,As discussed, it’s miraculous
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.02,0:15:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,how our bodies heal\Nand repair themselves when damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.19,0:15:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now think of this:\NIf you damage, scrape, or dent your car,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.86,0:15:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,does it heal itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.90,0:15:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardly!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.40,0:15:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What if every time we bruised, scraped,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.28,0:15:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,or damaged our body
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.70,0:15:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it just stayed that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.95,0:15:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In a short time,\Nwe’d get to looking pretty rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.96,0:15:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But the God who made our bodies\Nin this miraculous way
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.21,0:15:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly can heal all infirmities,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.05,0:15:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,reverse aging,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.05,0:15:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and prevent sickness in his new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.09,0:15:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And he has promised to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.35,0:15:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the third symposium
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.35,0:15:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,went back to our main book that builds faith\N—the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.69,0:16:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And we discussed those
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.82,0:16:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who acquired strong faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.94,0:16:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and we discussed how they did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.11,0:16:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And even though their contemporaries\Nwere faithless,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.57,0:16:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,they developed this faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.87,0:16:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, our faith was empowered
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.20,0:16:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as we discussed Abel, Enoch, Noah,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.83,0:16:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses, and Jesus’ disciples,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.13,0:16:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and we became more determined than ever
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.09,0:16:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to imitate these faithful ones
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.80,0:16:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and not their faithless contemporaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.22,0:16:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know we can be successful
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.97,0:16:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because we have the same Father, Helper,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.10,0:16:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Supplier of holy spirit as they had.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.98,0:16:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, our three symposiums on Friday
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.23,0:16:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,clearly showed us
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.28,0:16:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah answers our pleas for more faith\Nby means of two books
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.82,0:16:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—the Bible and the book of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.99,0:16:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But regarding our drama, we ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.37,0:17:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jehovah answer
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.58,0:17:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel’s pleas for more faith?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.25,0:17:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one way was\Nhe gave Daniel his written Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.51,0:17:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In the drama, if you recall,\NDaniel’s father gave him a scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.51,0:17:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that he regularly referred to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.47,0:17:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you recognize that scroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.85,0:17:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The scroll depicted in the drama
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.35,0:17:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is known today as Psalm 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.57,0:17:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When enemies tried to discredit Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.78,0:17:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw him reflect on Psalm 27:11, 12,\Nwhich says in part:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.78,0:17:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not hand me over to my adversaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.74,0:17:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“for false witnesses\Nhave risen up against me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.66,0:17:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and they threaten me with violence.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.79,0:17:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When he was threatened with execution,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.05,0:17:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw him reflect
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.05,0:17:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,on Psalm 27:7-9,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.59,0:17:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,which says in part:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.59,0:17:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“You are my helper;
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.60,0:17:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“do not forsake me or leave me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.47,0:18:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,my God of salvation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.06,0:18:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How those verses
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.06,0:18:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,would have bolstered Daniel’s faith!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.19,0:18:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we cannot say for sure\Nthat Daniel reflected
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.53,0:18:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,on those specific verses,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.11,0:18:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but the Bible does reveal that Daniel’s faith
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.66,0:18:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,indeed was strengthened by the Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.25,0:18:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know that Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.25,0:18:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,was a keen student of Bible prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.38,0:18:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He even said of himself at Daniel 9:2:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.34,0:18:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“I, Daniel, discerned by the books
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.76,0:18:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,[that is, the sacred books]\Nthe number of years.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.84,0:18:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he talks about the desolation\N(restoration) of Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.60,0:18:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,—“namely, 70 years.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.35,0:18:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we ask, Will Jehovah answer
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.15,0:18:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,our pleas for more faith?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.77,0:18:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Most definitely he will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.28,0:18:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And one outstanding way he has done this
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.24,0:18:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is by providing us with Bible prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.83,0:19:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Prophecies in the book of Daniel alone\Nhave helped millions
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.29,0:19:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to build rock-solid faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.21,0:19:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, the fulfilled prophecies
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.96,0:19:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,regarding the king of the north\Nand the king of the south
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.46,0:19:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,have been very faith-strengthening.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.09,0:19:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, let’s review the video on this topic
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.22,0:19:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that appeared in Brother Kenneth Cook’s\NMay broadcast.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.73,0:19:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy this powerful video.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.65,0:19:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel received a prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.65,0:19:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,about the coming of two rivals:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.65,0:19:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“the king of the north”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.53,0:19:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and “the king of the south.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.95,0:19:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How has it been fulfilled?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.71,0:19:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In the late 1800’s, the German Empire
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.71,0:19:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,became the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.75,0:19:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That government brought
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.21,0:19:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,its “power and . . . heart
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.51,0:19:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“against the king of the south
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.80,0:19:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,with a large army.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.43,0:20:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, its navy was
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.64,0:20:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the second largest on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.98,0:20:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who became the king of the south?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.10,0:20:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The alliance between Britain
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.11,0:20:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.32,0:20:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He fought during World War I
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.32,0:20:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“with an exceedingly large
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.32,0:20:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and mighty army.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.20,0:20:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He “swept away” and “humbled”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.62,0:20:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.99,0:20:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was not the end
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.41,0:20:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.50,0:20:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He turned his attention to and then hurled
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.63,0:20:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“denunciations against the holy covenant.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.25,0:20:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He removed “the constant feature”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.51,0:20:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,by limiting the freedom of God’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.51,0:20:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to preach,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.30,0:20:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,imprisoning many,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.56,0:20:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and even killing hundreds
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.60,0:20:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of God’s anointed ones
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.81,0:20:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and their fellow workers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.90,0:20:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,After Germany was defeated in World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.40,0:20:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the Soviet Union
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.44,0:20:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,became the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.53,0:21:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It worked with the king of the south
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.53,0:21:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to “put in place the disgusting thing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.91,0:21:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that causes desolation”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.41,0:21:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,—the United Nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.09,0:21:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Beginning in the early 1900’s,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.72,0:21:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the Soviet government tried to eliminate
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.01,0:21:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,religion in the lands under its control,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.35,0:21:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfilling the words
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.77,0:21:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that he would “show no regard
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.35,0:21:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for the God of his fathers.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.57,0:21:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave glory, not to the God of heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.44,0:21:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but “to the god of fortresses.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.36,0:21:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,As prophesied,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.95,0:21:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,he used this military might
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.78,0:21:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,against the king of the south
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.33,0:21:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by engaging “with him in a pushing.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.91,0:21:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Anglo-America competed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.96,0:21:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Soviet Union
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.08,0:21:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for world domination,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.04,0:21:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,fighting in and supporting wars
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.17,0:21:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and political struggles around the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.18,0:22:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,After the Soviet Union collapsed in 1991,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.89,0:22:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it was unclear who would fill the role\Nof the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.56,0:22:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,For a time, God’s people there
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.64,0:22:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,had been able to preach\Nand worship peacefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But in recent years, Russia and its allies
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.57,0:22:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,have pushed back at the king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.49,0:22:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Both kings have accused each other
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.49,0:22:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of destructive cyber and economic attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.54,0:22:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But the king of the north has not limited
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.95,0:22:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,his attacks to the king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.29,0:22:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As foretold, he also entered
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.38,0:22:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“into the land of the Decoration”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.75,0:22:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,—our realm of spiritual activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.34,0:22:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, Russian authorities continue
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.47,0:22:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to attack true worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.43,0:22:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We expect such persecution,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.56,0:22:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but we also expect it to end.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.16,0:23:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Our King, Jesus Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.29,0:23:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is more powerful than any human government.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.75,0:23:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon he will destroy\Nnot only the kings of the north and the south
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.26,0:23:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but all of his enemies,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.35,0:23:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will deliver God’s loyal people.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.71,0:24:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What a powerful video!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.26,0:24:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Has the unerring accuracy of those prophecies
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.80,0:24:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,strengthened your faith?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.72,0:24:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re confident that it has.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.85,0:24:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re absolutely convinced\Nthat the rest of that prophecy,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.69,0:24:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,including our deliverance,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.69,0:24:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,will be fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.90,0:24:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ soon will defend God’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.03,0:24:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring an end\Nto this entire wicked system.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.57,0:24:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,May all of us continue to study
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.49,0:24:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,these and other prophecies.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.87,0:24:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do, our faith
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.54,0:24:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in our wise, our all-powerful,\Nour loving Father
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.42,0:24:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,will definitely be strengthened.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.63,0:24:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But now let’s move to Saturday’s program,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.22,0:24:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,which had the theme taken from Jude 3:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.93,0:24:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“Put up a hard fight for the faith.”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.56,0:25:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The symposium\N“Successful Fighters for the Faith”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.11,0:25:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,showed that many who do not have a spouse
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.49,0:25:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and many whose spouse\Nis not yet serving Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.36,0:25:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,are winning their fight for the faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.66,0:25:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And we warmly commend
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.08,0:25:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you dear, beloved ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.12,0:25:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The baptism discourse\Nencouraged new disciples
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.25,0:25:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue strengthening their faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.59,0:25:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and we warmly welcome\Nall newly baptized ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.59,0:25:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah loves you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.01,0:25:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body loves you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.39,0:25:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brothers and sisters love you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.39,0:25:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re so happy to have you join us
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.23,0:25:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in our united family
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.73,0:25:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of intense fighters for the faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.78,0:25:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The two afternoon symposiums
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.49,0:25:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,helped us to analyze\Nhow we can show our faith
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.70,0:26:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,by giving of our time,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.87,0:26:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,energy, and material things
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.96,0:26:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to advance the Kingdom work\Nand to help others.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.80,0:26:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And we discussed some specific things\Nthat we may be able to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.18,0:26:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, learn a new language,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.68,0:26:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,move and serve where the need is greater,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.89,0:26:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,apply for the School\Nfor Kingdom Evangelizers,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.56,0:26:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,assist with a building project,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.23,0:26:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and “set something aside” for Jehovah’s work.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.11,0:26:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The talk “Put Up a Hard Fight for the Faith!”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.74,0:26:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,reminded us that as is true in all fights
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.00,0:26:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—in our fight—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.00,0:26:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,we have enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.25,0:26:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing, we must reject apostate lies
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.34,0:26:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and the false stories of other opposers,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.84,0:26:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which are designed to sow doubt\Nand weaken faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.30,0:26:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan is very skilled
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.97,0:27:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,at using innuendo, half-truths, and lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.68,0:27:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s not surprising that the news media
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.61,0:27:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,—which is often manipulated by apostates,\Nclergymen, and other opposers—
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.61,0:27:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,likewise often employs innuendo,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.95,0:27:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,half-truths, and lies
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.41,0:27:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,against Jehovah’s organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.24,0:27:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about this:\NFaith is a product of holy spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.83,0:27:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a provision from Jehovah\Nto strengthen us,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.55,0:27:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,whereas doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.71,0:27:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is a tool of the Devil designed to weaken us.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.80,0:27:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you recall how Satan approached Eve?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.64,0:27:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“Is it really so
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.77,0:27:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that God said you must not eat\Nfrom every tree of the garden?”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.15,0:27:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Is that really so?’
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.40,0:27:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did he present it that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.57,0:27:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,To plant doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.57,0:27:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and ‘shipwreck her faith,’ and he succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.86,0:28:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, likewise, if we’re not careful,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.37,0:28:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,doubt can shipwreck our faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.25,0:28:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But strong faith
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.29,0:28:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,keeps doubt out of our hearts and minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.54,0:28:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, in talking just a little bit more\Nabout apostates,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.13,0:28:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,what if an apostate knocked\Nat your front door and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.34,0:28:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’d like to come into your home,\NI’d like to sit down with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.43,0:28:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’d like to teach you\Nsome apostate ideas”?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.23,0:28:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, you would immediately\Nget rid of him, wouldn’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.44,0:28:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You would send him down the highway.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.36,0:28:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But now think of this:\NWhat if that same apostate
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.07,0:28:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,tries to come into your home\Nby means of the television
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.70,0:28:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,or computer?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.70,0:28:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, hopefully, we reject him
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.79,0:28:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,just as decisively.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.54,0:28:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Second John 10 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.29,0:28:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“If anyone comes to you\Nand does not bring this teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.96,0:28:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[never] receive him into your homes”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.92,0:29:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—that would mean not through the front door,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.14,0:29:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,not through the television, or computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.01,0:29:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, though, some have reasoned foolishly:
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.68,0:29:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,‘If I listen to this apostate\Non television or the computer
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.40,0:29:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‘or perhaps read his book,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.52,0:29:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’ll recognize how wrong he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.44,0:29:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‘It’ll build up my faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.53,0:29:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,‘And if I ever encounter this teaching\Nin the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.07,0:29:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll better be able to refute it.’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.24,0:29:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that is foolish thinking indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.25,0:29:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be like reasoning,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.50,0:29:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,‘If I eat stinky, rotten, food\Nfrom a garbage can,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.00,0:29:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,‘it will really help me in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.17,0:29:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to recognize bad food.’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.34,0:29:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not very good reasoning, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.76,0:29:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than feed our minds\Npoisonous, apostate ideas,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.35,0:29:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we read God’s Word daily
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.94,0:29:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and strengthen and safeguard our faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.40,0:30:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we ask, How did Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.11,0:30:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,put up a hard fight for the faith?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.82,0:30:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for one thing, he resisted pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.24,0:30:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to compromise.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.24,0:30:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But can you imagine the pressure\Nhe must have faced
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.41,0:30:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,when offered the king’s delicacies and wine?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.63,0:30:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How was he able to refuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.21,0:30:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for the answer,\Nlet’s go to Daniel chapter 1, please,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.22,0:30:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s read verse number 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.56,0:30:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel 1:8: “But Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.43,0:30:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“resolved in his heart
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.60,0:30:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“that he would not defile himself\Nwith the king’s delicacies
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.07,0:30:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“or with the wine he drank.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.40,0:30:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“So he asked the principal court official\Nfor permission
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.07,0:30:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,not to defile himself in this way.”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.74,0:30:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So notice, in advance,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.29,0:30:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel “resolved in his heart”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.29,0:30:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the course he was going to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.79,0:31:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And he did so because he was fully convinced
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.46,0:31:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that whatever Jehovah had commanded
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.13,0:31:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,was for his good.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.39,0:31:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, like Daniel, we must put up\Na hard fight for the faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.27,0:31:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you facing pressure right now
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.02,0:31:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,—at school, at work, or even at home—
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.27,0:31:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to compromise?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.32,0:31:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, please don’t give up
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.11,0:31:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and don’t give in.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.49,0:31:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Reflect on Daniel’s example,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.37,0:31:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and fight for your faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.08,0:31:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Be resolved to obey Jehovah because doing so
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.67,0:31:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is always the right thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.67,0:31:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you do, you will have no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.92,0:31:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Pressure was also put on Daniel\Nby means of threats.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.43,0:31:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But can you imagine how Daniel felt\Nwhen he became aware
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.85,0:31:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that his next prayer\Ncould lead to his execution?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.56,0:32:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped him to stay loyal?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.57,0:32:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s go to Daniel chapter 6
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.53,0:32:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and get some help with that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.70,0:32:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel chapter 6
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.28,0:32:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and, please, let’s read together\Nverse number 10:
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.75,0:32:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“But as soon as Daniel knew
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.33,0:32:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“that the decree had been signed,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.00,0:32:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“he went to his house,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.00,0:32:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“which had the windows of his roof chamber\Nopen toward Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.05,0:32:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“And three times a day\Nhe got down on his knees
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.80,0:32:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“and prayed and offered praise\Nbefore his God,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.14,0:32:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“[now notice] as he had regularly done
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.44,0:32:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,prior to this.”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.73,0:32:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So Daniel knew what was right,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.36,0:32:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and he didn’t hesitate to do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.65,0:32:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was consistent in his worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.24,0:32:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel 6:16 tells us
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.82,0:32:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that Daniel\Nwas “continually serving” his God.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.04,0:32:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}The Watchtower {
} explains\Nthat the original Bible word
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.25,0:33:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,translated “continually serving”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.42,0:33:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,basically means to “move in a circle,”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.92,0:33:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which suggests continuity.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.92,0:33:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And how well that describes\NDaniel’s unbroken worship!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.85,0:33:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,See, there’s no end to a circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.56,0:33:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s unbroken, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.14,0:33:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Please watch the following dramatization
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.65,0:33:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that depicts a brother\Nwho faces a threat of being arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.32,0:33:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But by reflecting on Daniel’s example,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.78,0:33:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,he is helped to continue serving Jehovah\Nwith constancy
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.78,0:33:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in the face\Nof this intimidating circumstance.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.42,0:33:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s still chaos in many parts of the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.38,0:33:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with armed soldiers detaining and arresting
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.30,0:33:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,those not pledging support
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.17,0:33:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of the new government.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.17,0:33:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we still going to the meeting tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.76,0:33:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to do what was best
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.76,0:33:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,for my wife and daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.56,0:34:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But a few of the elders
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.19,0:34:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,have already been arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.52,0:34:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I was arrested?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.25,0:34:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What would happen to my family?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.15,0:34:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re not going home to pray, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.15,0:34:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I pray at my window three times a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.99,0:34:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.82,0:35:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If I even appear to compromise,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.29,0:35:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what would they think?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.08,0:35:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.17,0:35:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I trust him,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.00,0:35:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,he’ll reward me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.17,0:35:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know how,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.22,0:35:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but he will.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.26,0:35:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray that I keep my faith
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.93,0:35:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,—that we all keep our faith—
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.73,0:35:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter how this ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.90,0:35:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The Scriptures are clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.07,0:35:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We must continue to meet together,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.95,0:35:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,even in small groups if necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.66,0:35:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s just pray that whatever happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.87,0:35:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the strength to endure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.67,0:35:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear Jehovah God, please . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.21,0:35:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, I was arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.06,0:36:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We miss you so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.14,0:36:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but we’re very proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.19,0:36:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We know whatever the outcome of your trial,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.90,0:36:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll maintain your faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.94,0:36:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and so will we.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.07,0:36:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.78,0:36:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very scared,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.70,0:36:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah helps us when we’re scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.58,0:36:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I would be OK
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.79,0:36:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.42,0:36:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,would take care of my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.18,0:36:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As was true of the brother in our video,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.68,0:36:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we will be persecuted.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.68,0:36:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Timothy 3:12 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.06,0:36:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“All those desiring to live\Nwith godly devotion
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.56,0:36:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“in association with Christ Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.27,0:36:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,will also be persecuted.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.94,0:37:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn’t say maybe, good chance, probably
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.20,0:37:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,—‘will be persecuted.’
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.24,0:37:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s guaranteed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.99,0:37:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But like our brother in the video,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.12,0:37:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,when persecuted,\Nlet’s reflect on Daniel’s example
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.83,0:37:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s fight for our faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.09,0:37:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And then let’s pray,\Nconfident that our God
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.09,0:37:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is always mightier than our enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.22,0:37:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s be like young David\Nwhen he went out to meet Goliath.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.56,0:37:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, David saw the big picture, didn’t he?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.56,0:37:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, he saw how big Goliath was,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.02,0:37:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but in the big picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.02,0:37:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he saw how puny Goliath was
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.44,0:37:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,compared to his almighty God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.78,0:37:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In a unique way, Daniel also experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.28,0:37:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,how mighty Jehovah is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.37,0:37:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,when he was thrown into the lions’ pit.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.04,0:37:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah sent an angel\Nto shut the mouths of those lions.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.79,0:37:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, think about it: Those lions\Nobviously were very hungry
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.01,0:38:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because a little bit later\Nwhen people were thrown in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.34,0:38:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they were consumed\Nbefore they hit the bottom of the pit.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.72,0:38:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So they were very hungry,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.72,0:38:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and Daniel would have looked\Nlike a tasty morsel.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.14,0:38:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But no matter how hard they tried,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.98,0:38:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,those lions couldn’t get their mouths open
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.40,0:38:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to harm Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.15,0:38:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel also set a good example
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.99,0:38:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in remaining hopeful despite old age
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.62,0:38:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and infirmities.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.74,0:38:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But can you imagine how Daniel felt\Nwhen he was almost 100 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.46,0:38:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and many Jews left\Nfor their beloved homeland, Judah,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.88,0:38:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was unable to go with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.30,0:38:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But what helped him to keep his hope alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.18,0:38:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s go to Daniel chapter 10, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.47,0:38:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see one thing that helped Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.47,0:38:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In Daniel chapter 10 and beginning\Nin verse 18, Daniel says:
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.19,0:38:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“The one who looked like a man\Ntouched me again
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.77,0:38:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“and strengthened me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.90,0:39:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then he said: ‘Do not be afraid,\NO very precious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.78,0:39:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘May you have peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.78,0:39:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be strong, yes, be strong.’
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.66,0:39:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“As he spoke with me I was strengthened
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.41,0:39:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“and I said: ‘Let my lord speak,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.29,0:39:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,for you have strengthened me.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.34,0:39:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So through an angel, Jehovah reassured Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.84,0:39:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was precious\Nand still very useful to Him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.85,0:39:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Daniel accepted\Nthe encouragement, didn’t he?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.93,0:39:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And thereafter, Jehovah\Ngave him a thrilling prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.85,0:39:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,about the king of the north\Nand the king of the south, which he recorded
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.23,0:39:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for our benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.24,0:39:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Although old and infirm, this precious man
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.28,0:39:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,was still very useful to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.66,0:39:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Please watch the following dramatization
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.41,0:39:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in which an older brother who feels helpless
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.67,0:40:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,reflects on how the angel reassured Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.31,0:40:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It all went by so quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.98,0:40:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,—pioneering,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.69,0:40:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,foreign language,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.74,0:40:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,circuit work.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.57,0:40:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There was even a time
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.57,0:40:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was the one encouraging older ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.45,0:40:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I miss those days so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.42,0:40:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I’m the one in a nursing home.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.17,0:40:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I feel like I have
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.55,0:40:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing left to offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.85,0:41:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,O Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.06,0:41:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you very precious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.32,0:41:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been sent to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.41,0:41:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not be afraid, Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.70,0:41:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Your words have been heard
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.99,0:41:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,from the first day you gave your heart
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.24,0:41:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.66,0:41:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.42,0:41:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no breath left in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.50,0:41:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not be afraid, O very precious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.88,0:41:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,May you have peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.92,0:41:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.63,0:41:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Be strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.85,0:41:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy is the one who keeps in expectation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.35,0:41:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.73,0:41:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You will rest, but you will stand up
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.94,0:41:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for your lot at the end of the days.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.11,0:41:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, just checking on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.45,0:41:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.70,0:41:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s something I’ve been wanting
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.95,0:41:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to share with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.79,0:41:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.96,0:42:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Jehovah does remember me,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.55,0:42:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and I still have much to offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.52,0:42:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a very touching video indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.40,0:42:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we ask, Do you have infirmities
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.94,0:42:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that keep you from doing\Nwhat you would like to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.07,0:42:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, reflect on Daniel’s example
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.86,0:42:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and accept Jehovah’s reassurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.24,0:42:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And remember that what you used to do
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.66,0:42:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is still viewed as valuable to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.37,0:42:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He will not forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.87,0:42:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And your present acts of faithfulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.09,0:42:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,even if small,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.13,0:42:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,are very precious to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.05,0:42:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We entreat all of you:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.26,0:42:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether young or old,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.30,0:43:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,like Daniel, do not stop
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.22,0:43:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,putting up a hard fight for the faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.64,0:43:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But now let’s talk about today’s program,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.77,0:43:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which has the theme taken from Matthew 21:21:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.07,0:43:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“If you have faith . . . , it will happen.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.87,0:43:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In the morning, we enjoyed\Nthe faith-strengthening symposium
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.58,0:43:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“Imitate Women of Strong Faith!”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.71,0:43:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And in each of the eight parts,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.79,0:43:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the exemplary women of faith\Nwho were discussed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.50,0:43:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,faced mountainlike obstacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.47,0:43:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sarah had to leave a comfortable lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.55,0:43:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for a nomadic lifestyle,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.56,0:43:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and for many years, she suffered barrenness.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.60,0:43:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Rahab had to take decisive action\N—risk her life—
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.61,0:43:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to protect the Israelite spies
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.19,0:43:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and take a stand with God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.28,0:44:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thereafter, she had to give up\Nan immoral lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.28,0:44:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hannah continued to serve Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.04,0:44:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,while enduring many years of barrenness\Nand harassment from Peninnah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.37,0:44:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The captive Israelite girl
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.42,0:44:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,was forcibly separated from her family
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.13,0:44:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by Syrian marauders
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.76,0:44:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but nevertheless continued\Nto fearlessly witness
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.60,0:44:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to others about Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.85,0:44:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary accepted the difficult assignment
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.64,0:44:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of giving birth to, caring for,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.73,0:44:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and training God’s Son.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.19,0:44:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The Phoenician woman\Ncourageously and persistently
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.45,0:44:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,sought help from Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.86,0:44:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for her demon-possessed daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.28,0:44:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And she got that help, didn’t she?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.16,0:44:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Martha, after the painful loss\Nof her brother to the enemy death,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.67,0:44:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,maintained faith in Jesus’ ability
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.25,0:44:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to raise the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.76,0:44:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The two modern-day examples\Nthat we discussed in the last talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.63,0:45:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Sisters Ishii and Toom,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.01,0:45:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,both steadfastly refused to compromise
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.06,0:45:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,despite being imprisoned for many years
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.44,0:45:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,simply because they were\NJehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.90,0:45:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, each one of these dear sisters faced
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.73,0:45:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,mountainlike obstacles
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.57,0:45:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah rewarded their faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.99,0:45:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Their faith moved them\Nto expect good things from Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.54,0:45:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah never ever let them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.08,0:45:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what good things\Ndo we expect from Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.38,0:45:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,if we maintain strong faith?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.05,0:45:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s talk about some of the events
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.13,0:45:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that we expect to unfold in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.43,0:45:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for one thing, the final part\Nof Nebuchadnezzar’s image dream
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.27,0:45:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,discussed in Daniel chapter 2\Nwill be fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.02,0:45:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As represented by the four upper parts\Nof that image,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.44,0:46:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,four world powers have come and gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.36,0:46:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,just as prophesied.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.57,0:46:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, the Anglo-American World Power,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.41,0:46:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,symbolized by the feet of iron and clay,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.33,0:46:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is dominating.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.33,0:46:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And more than ever,\Nwe see this last world power
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.50,0:46:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,living up to being a noncohesive mixture
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.09,0:46:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of iron and clay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.38,0:46:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And just as iron mixed with clay
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.14,0:46:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is weaker than solid iron,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.72,0:46:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so too the Anglo-American World Power\Nis weaker
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.93,0:46:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,than the ironlike Roman Empire\Nfrom which it emerged.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.31,0:46:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The ability of the Anglo-American World Power\Nto act with ironlike strength
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.03,0:46:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is weakened by claylike elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.91,0:46:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,such as people rising up\Nto claim their rights
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.66,0:46:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,through insurrection,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.75,0:46:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,civil rights campaigns,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.58,0:46:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and independence movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.50,0:47:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,As Daniel foretold in chapter 2, verse 42:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.09,0:47:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“The kingdom will be partly strong
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.18,0:47:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and partly fragile.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.47,0:47:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that is\Nmore and more evident today than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.10,0:47:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But despite the weakened condition\Nof this final world power,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.02,0:47:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it will not simply disintegrate\Ninto self-destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.03,0:47:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to Daniel chapter 2,\Nand let’s notice how it comes to its end.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.03,0:47:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a very familiar scripture here\N—Daniel 2:44:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.16,0:47:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“In the days of those kings the God of heaven
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.62,0:47:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“will set up a kingdom\Nthat will never be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.67,0:47:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“And this kingdom will not be passed on\Nto any other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.80,0:47:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“It will crush and put an end\Nto all these kingdoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.68,0:47:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“and it alone will stand forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.35,0:47:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“just as you saw that out of the mountain\Na stone was cut not by hands
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.35,0:48:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“[that is, not by human hands,\Nbut by Jehovah’s hands],
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.02,0:48:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“and that it crushed the iron, the copper,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.23,0:48:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“the clay, the silver, and the gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.65,0:48:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Grand God has made known to the king\Nwhat will happen in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.16,0:48:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“The dream is true,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.16,0:48:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and its interpretation is trustworthy.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.21,0:48:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This scripture describes how God’s Kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.63,0:48:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,represented by that stone,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.96,0:48:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,will crush all human governments
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.84,0:48:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,at Armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.84,0:48:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And interestingly, at Daniel 2:34,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.85,0:48:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it tells us that ‘the stone [God’s Kingdom]
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.81,0:48:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,‘will strike the image\N[representing human governments]
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.15,0:48:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in the feet of iron and clay,’
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.36,0:48:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,clearly identifying that Armageddon will come
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.24,0:48:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,during the time\Nof the Anglo-American World Power
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.24,0:48:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,—the final human world power.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.16,0:48:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And like Daniel, we have strong faith
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.83,0:49:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in the last sentence of verse 45, which says:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.21,0:49:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“The dream is true, and its interpretation
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.88,0:49:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is trustworthy.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.97,0:49:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no doubt about it:\NGod’s Kingdom will destroy
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.64,0:49:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,all human governments at Armageddon
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.93,0:49:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,during the time\Nof the Anglo-American World Power.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.14,0:49:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, just as the final part\Nof the image dream
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.44,0:49:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,will soon be fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.57,0:49:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the final part of Daniel’s vision\Nin chapter 7
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.11,0:49:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,will soon be fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.11,0:49:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in chapter 7,\NDaniel describes four wild beasts,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.12,0:49:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which symbolize four world powers\Nthat have come and gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.12,0:49:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And appropriately,\Nthey’re described as wild beasts
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.05,0:49:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because they haven’t ruled kindly
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.09,0:49:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but, rather, in a harsh, beastly way.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.93,0:49:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, those four world powers
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.30,0:49:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,are Babylon, Medo-Persia, Greece, and Rome
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.72,0:50:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,—the very same four world powers
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.18,0:50:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,represented by the four upper metal parts
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.94,0:50:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of the image dream we discussed previously.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.40,0:50:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But in verse 8, Daniel describes a horn
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.28,0:50:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that grew out of the head\Nof that fourth beast—out of Rome;
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.12,0:50:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that horn had eyes; that horn had a mouth;
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.58,0:50:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that mouth spoke arrogantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.96,0:50:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this arrogant horn symbolizes
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.80,0:50:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the Anglo-American World Power
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.17,0:50:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,—again, the last world power.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.72,0:50:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what was foretold to happen next?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.43,0:50:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll go to Daniel chapter 7, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.48,0:50:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see what happens next.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.60,0:50:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel chapter 7,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.65,0:50:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and please let’s begin in verse number 26:
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.48,0:50:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the Court sat,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.07,0:50:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“and they took away his rulership\N[that is, that horn’s rulership],
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.91,0:51:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“in order to annihilate him\Nand to destroy him completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.50,0:51:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the kingdom and the rulership\Nand the grandeur
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.50,0:51:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“of the kingdoms under all the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.50,0:51:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“were given to the people
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.50,0:51:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“who are the holy ones of the Supreme One.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.01,0:51:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“Their kingdom is an everlasting kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.60,0:51:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and all rulerships will serve and obey them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.52,0:51:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The rulership of this arrogant horn\Nis taken away,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.69,0:51:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is annihilated and destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.02,0:51:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and replaced by God’s Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.49,0:51:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So just as described\Nin the imagery in this vision,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.41,0:51:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that God’s Kingdom\Ndestroys all human governments
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.95,0:51:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,during the time\Nof the Anglo-American World Power
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.58,0:51:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and then takes over rulership of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.50,0:51:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How exciting that event,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.42,0:51:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which will take place\Nin the near future, will be!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.13,0:52:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But think about it: Every preceding part\Nof that prophecy has come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.14,0:52:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have complete confidence, strong faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.10,0:52:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that the final part of it\Nwill also come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.11,0:52:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there are many other prophecies\Nin the book of Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.61,0:52:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that we didn’t have time to discuss
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.82,0:52:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that have come true in amazing detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.95,0:52:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But the fulfillment of so many prophecies
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.58,0:52:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,totally convinces us
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.83,0:52:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are deep, deep\Nin “the time of the end.”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.21,0:52:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Very soon, we’re going to witness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.88,0:52:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the fulfillment of Daniel 12:1,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.76,0:52:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,which talks about ‘Michael the great prince
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.35,0:52:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,standing up.’
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.35,0:52:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“And there will occur\Na time of [great] distress.”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.81,0:52:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But God’s “people will escape,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.31,0:52:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone who is found\Nwritten down in the book.”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.94,0:52:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In the video near the beginning of this talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.70,0:53:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw Michael, the glorified Jesus Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.70,0:53:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,depicted as coming with the angels
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.20,0:53:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to rescue Jehovah’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.54,0:53:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and destroy this wicked system.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.33,0:53:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, if you notice carefully\Nin that video,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.34,0:53:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the wicked were actually shooting\Ntheir weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.55,0:53:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,into the sky at Michael.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.84,0:53:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that’s laughable\N—isn’t it?—
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.47,0:53:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because mankind’s most powerful weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.35,0:53:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,are like wet firecrackers
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.94,0:53:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,compared to Michael’s mighty power.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.73,0:53:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, in the video,\NMichael was depicted as coming
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.23,0:53:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,with no defensive equipment,\Nsuch as a breastplate or shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.91,0:53:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.91,0:53:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He was depicted only with a sword
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.99,0:53:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—an offensive weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.04,0:53:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, sometimes in our illustrations,\Nhe’s depicted with a bow and arrow
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.63,0:53:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,—again, only an offensive weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.05,0:54:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But his offensive weapons are powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.55,0:54:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,—much, much more powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.01,0:54:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,than needed to do the job\Nof rescuing Jehovah’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.02,0:54:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and sweeping out of existence
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.06,0:54:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan’s entire wicked system.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.19,0:54:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But then after Armageddon,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.52,0:54:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the glorious Thousand Year Reign
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.82,0:54:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of Christ Jesus will begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.90,0:54:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And during that marvelous time,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.70,0:54:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the last verse
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.95,0:54:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of the book of Daniel will be fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.12,0:54:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.33,0:54:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The last verse of this book, chapter 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.42,0:54:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s read verse 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.92,0:54:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And here’s what was said to Daniel:
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.38,0:54:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“But as for you, go on to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.68,0:54:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“You will rest, but you will stand up
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.56,0:54:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for your lot at the end of the days.”
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.27,0:54:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Daniel served Jehovah faithfully
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.73,0:54:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,until the end of his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.86,0:54:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He went “to the end,” didn’t he?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.94,0:55:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he’s resting in death,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.78,0:55:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but soon he “will stand up”\Nin the resurrection
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.74,0:55:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,during Christ’s Millennial Reign
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.74,0:55:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“for [his] lot”—his place in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.58,0:55:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But we ask, Did Daniel have faith\Nin that promise
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.79,0:55:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah gave him through the angel?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.55,0:55:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For a certainty, he did!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.34,0:55:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He had already demonstrated\Nfaith for decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.63,0:55:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He remained clean when tempted to eat food
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.97,0:55:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that would defile him.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.27,0:55:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He was diligent in prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.27,0:55:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,even when praying meant\Nthat he would be executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.44,0:55:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He never stopped building his faith\Nthrough Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.44,0:55:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can be sure\Nhe believed with all his heart
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.03,0:55:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that promise Jehovah gave him\Nthrough the angel
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.33,0:55:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,—that he would stand up in the resurrection
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.83,0:55:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and take his place in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.41,0:55:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.42,0:56:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we maintain our faith
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.67,0:56:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as Daniel did?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.67,0:56:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, by staying morally\Nand spiritually clean,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.22,0:56:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,not allowing anything to corrupt our faith;
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.72,0:56:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,by praying constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.31,0:56:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with full confidence that Jehovah\Nwill answer our prayers;
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.10,0:56:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and by listening to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.27,0:56:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,by diligent study of his Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.32,0:56:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah wants us to have faith
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.45,0:56:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that he is our Rewarder.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.41,0:56:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hebrews 11:6 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.58,0:56:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whoever approaches God must believe\Nthat he is [that he’s really there]
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.58,0:56:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“and that he becomes the rewarder
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.50,0:56:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of those earnestly seeking him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.38,0:56:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about our two brothers\Nshown earlier in this talk:
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.51,0:56:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the Christian father and the sick brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.51,0:56:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The Christian father ended up behind bars,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.81,0:56:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and our sick brother\Nwas not miraculously healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.60,0:57:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So was their faith in vain?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.40,0:57:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,For a certainty, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.48,0:57:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Will Jehovah reward them?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.82,0:57:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,For a certainty, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.95,0:57:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are facing a similar situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.24,0:57:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,will Jehovah reward you?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.33,0:57:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Most definitely yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.75,0:57:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Please watch the following video
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.67,0:57:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,which features the song that we will sing
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.96,0:57:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to conclude our convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.47,0:57:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.20,0:57:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should I fear the lion?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.33,0:58:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should I fear any foe?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.92,0:58:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah by my side,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.84,0:58:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not run and hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.26,0:58:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,My God is with me; this I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.18,0:58:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.81,0:58:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I see beyond the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.19,0:58:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.78,0:58:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s nothing more to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.32,0:58:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah, I am strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.20,0:58:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Determined to go on,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.08,0:58:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing that my God is always near—
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.54,0:58:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.97,0:59:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Those faithful ones before us
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.36,0:59:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Lived their lives in loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.53,0:59:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,By their faith they endured.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.32,0:59:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Their future is assured.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.74,0:59:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll stand again for all to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.75,0:59:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.42,0:59:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I see beyond the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.55,0:59:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.01,0:59:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s nothing more to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.64,0:59:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah, I am strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.31,0:59:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Determined to go on,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.44,0:59:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing that my God is always near—
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.15,0:59:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.37,1:00:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith, I can move a mountain.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.29,1:00:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith, my hope is sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.42,1:00:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would I be
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.67,1:00:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the faith that helps me see
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.01,1:00:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond the trials I endure?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.77,1:00:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I see the wondrous future
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.57,1:00:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,God has in store for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.12,1:00:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to be strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.29,1:00:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it won’t be long
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.46,1:00:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Till Jehovah claims his victory.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.88,1:00:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.47,1:01:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I see beyond the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.80,1:01:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.22,1:01:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s nothing more to fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.85,1:01:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah, I am strong,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.77,1:01:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Determined to go on,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.53,1:01:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing that my God is always near—
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.87,1:01:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.76,1:01:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.56,1:01:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What a powerfully motivating video!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.44,1:01:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And we look forward to singing that song
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.19,1:02:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to conclude our convention.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.66,1:02:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.99,1:02:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,faithful children,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.99,1:02:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,cherished interested ones,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.54,1:02:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s no doubt that right now
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.67,1:02:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we face powerful enemies.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.17,1:02:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing, we have a powerful enemy
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.59,1:02:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,inside our bodies
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.63,1:02:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,—inherited sin.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.64,1:02:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It wages an intense war\Nagainst our desire to do what is right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.68,1:02:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondly, we have the formidable foes:
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.69,1:02:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan and his demons.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.77,1:02:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan is described as a devouring lion,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.36,1:02:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a cunning serpent,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.36,1:02:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a fierce dragon,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.45,1:02:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a sneaky birdcatcher,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.45,1:02:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s given other evil descriptions.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.16,1:02:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ephesians 6:12 says:
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.58,1:02:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“We have a struggle\N[the footnote, literally “a wrestling”]
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.08,1:03:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . against the wicked spirit forces\Nin the heavenly places.”
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.09,1:03:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And as mentioned in our publications,\Nthere may be tens of thousands
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.39,1:03:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of these powerful, evil spirit creatures
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.81,1:03:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in the invisible realm
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.81,1:03:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,waging war against us.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.15,1:03:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirdly, we have this wicked world\Nall around us
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.65,1:03:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that is trying to assimilate us
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.40,1:03:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,into joining them in ungodly conduct.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.78,1:03:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And looking at the ratio,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.95,1:03:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we as Jehovah’s people\Nare outnumbered by people of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.21,1:03:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by about 900 to 1.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.75,1:03:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But despite the power\Nof those three great enemies,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.55,1:03:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,our faith—this product\Nof Jehovah’s invincible holy spirit—
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.30,1:03:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,makes us stronger and stronger individually
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.27,1:03:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,than all of those three enemies combined.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.61,1:04:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In the near future,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.65,1:04:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,another powerful enemy will come against us.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.99,1:04:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This formidable foe
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.86,1:04:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is a coalition of nations\Ncalled Gog in Ezekiel chapter 38.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.87,1:04:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And Ezekiel chapter 38 says\Nthat Gog will come with “a great assembly,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.87,1:04:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a vast army.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.96,1:04:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“Like clouds covering the land,”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.55,1:04:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,they will come against God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.22,1:04:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this could be\Na very intimidating situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.80,1:04:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But dear brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.80,1:04:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,your faith will make you stronger than Gog
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.81,1:04:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and will keep you strong
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.10,1:04:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,until Jehovah miraculously intervenes\Nat Armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.02,1:04:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you think about it,\NArmageddon really is a rescue operation.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.65,1:04:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He will intervene,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.65,1:04:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will sweep attacking Gog away forever
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.49,1:04:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,with a “broom of annihilation.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.54,1:05:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past, faith has helped God’s people
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.88,1:05:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to overcome the most powerful obstacles,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.05,1:05:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and that same product of holy spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.01,1:05:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,will help us do the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.22,1:05:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, throughout the centuries,\Njust like today,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.51,1:05:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s servants, such as Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.93,1:05:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,have been made powerful,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.02,1:05:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,not by natural strength, but through faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.94,1:05:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So dear brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.74,1:05:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,faithful children,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.07,1:05:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,cherished interested ones,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.62,1:05:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,pray earnestly for faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.12,1:05:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Put up a hard fight to maintain your faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.50,1:05:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And trust with all your heart
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.04,1:05:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that if you have faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.04,1:05:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,maintain your faith, and walk by faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.38,1:05:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you definitely will see
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.05,1:05:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,all of Jehovah’s promises fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.06,1:05:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Lett.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.18,1:06:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Your talk and this entire convention
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.73,1:06:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,have strengthened our faith\Nand prepared us for future events.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.28,1:06:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All in attendance will be pleased to know
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.61,1:06:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that Parts I and II of the drama 
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.24,1:06:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Daniel: A Lifetime of Faith
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.83,1:06:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,are available now for download on jw.org
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.41,1:06:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}JW Library® {
}app.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.67,1:06:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This convention is further proof that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.59,1:06:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and his Son, Jesus Christ,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.30,1:06:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,provide abundantly for our spiritual needs
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.47,1:06:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,despite difficult world conditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.56,1:06:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How we rejoice to be in their loving care!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.40,1:06:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And on behalf of the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.48,1:06:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the hardworking members\Nof our Bethel families
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.94,1:06:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and translation offices around the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.32,1:06:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we thank you for watching
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.66,1:06:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the 2021 regional convention program.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.41,1:07:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.41,1:07:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,May your love and faith remain strong,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.88,1:07:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and may your hope remain bright.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.04,1:07:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,From the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.51,1:07:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting®.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.09,1:07:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s conclude now by singing a song
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.56,1:07:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that expresses the power\Nthat faith has in our lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.35,1:07:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Please join in singing the original song
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.73,1:07:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“With Eyes of Faith,”
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.98,1:07:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which we heard sung\Nduring the concluding talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.82,1:07:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,After the song,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.99,1:07:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you may have your concluding prayer\Nat your individual locations.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.91,1:07:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we invite all to sing out
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.04,1:07:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,along with the Watchtower chorus\N“With Eyes of Faith.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.41,0:00:18.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,今見たドラマを含め\Nこの地区大会のプログラムには
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.46,0:00:23.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,100を超えるビデオやオーディオの\Nコンテンツが含まれています
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.29,0:00:27.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオは世界中のいろいろな\N場所で制作されています
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.17,0:00:33.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはそうした王国の活動を\N金銭面で支えられます
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.10,0:00:36.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,オンラインで寄付を行うことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.89,0:00:41.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,donate.jw.orgを\Nご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.69,0:00:45.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドラマで見たように
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.73,0:00:51.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは試練に遭っても\N老齢になっても 強い信仰を保ちました
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.32,0:00:54.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちもそうできるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.24,0:00:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが見た幻から\Nどのように力が得られますか
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.08,0:01:03.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体のスティーブン・レット兄弟の\N話に注目しましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.21,0:01:07.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,結びの話の中で\N疑問に答えてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.30,0:01:11.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,題は 「信仰によって\N強くなりましょう！」です
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.54,0:01:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,鉄筋コンクリートで建てられた建物は
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.04,0:01:26.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,強い地震に持ちこたえることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.92,0:01:30.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,地中の深くに根を張った頑丈な木は
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.55,0:01:34.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,嵐に何度遭っても\N倒れることがありません
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.01,0:01:39.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,厳しいトレーニングを受けて\N自分を鍛え上げた運動選手は
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.77,0:01:43.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,デカスロンと呼ばれる10種目競技を
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.60,0:01:47.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後まで行うことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.48,0:01:49.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,建物がしっかり立ち
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.90,0:01:54.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,木や運動選手が強くなれるように
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.49,0:01:57.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕える私たちも
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.20,0:02:01.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰によって強くなることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.87,0:02:05.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,この話では 宇宙で最も強力な力である
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.83,0:02:09.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖なる力が生み出す信仰によって
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.09,0:02:12.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように強くなれるかを学びます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.38,0:02:14.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰によって強くなっていれば
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.59,0:02:17.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな問題や試練や誘惑も
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.76,0:02:20.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,乗り越えることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.39,0:02:22.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分にはあまり体力がないとか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.77,0:02:25.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,精神面で強くないと思うかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.90,0:02:29.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも信仰があれば\Nエホバとの絆が強まります
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.94,0:02:32.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの絆が強いことは
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.11,0:02:37.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,体力があることや精神面で\N強いことよりもはるかに大切です
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.87,0:02:42.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの絆が強ければ\Nアブラハムのようになれます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.66,0:02:45.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,ローマ 4章を開いてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.33,0:02:47.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,アブラハムについて述べられています
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.92,0:02:50.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,18節から読みます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.01,0:02:53.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,「かないそうにない希望でしたが
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.30,0:02:57.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでもアブラハムは希望に\N基づいて信仰を持ちました
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.93,0:03:02.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,『あなたの子孫も星のように\N多くなる』と言われた通り
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.18,0:03:06.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの国の人々の\N父祖となることを信じたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.52,0:03:11.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の体がすでに死んだも同然である\N（およそ100歳だった）ことや
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.78,0:03:15.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,サラが子供を産めなくなって\Nいることを考えましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.32,0:03:18.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰は弱くなりませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.28,0:03:23.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の約束があったので 信仰が欠けて\Nふらつくということはなく
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.91,0:03:27.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,かえって［次に注目してください］
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.17,0:03:30.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰によって強くなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.59,0:03:34.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 神をたたえ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.67,0:03:40.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,神が約束を必ず果たされる\Nということを確信していました」
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.47,0:03:45.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,アブラハムは100歳近くに\Nなっていました
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:51.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,体力も衰え 感情面でも弱さを\N感じることがあったかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.36,0:03:54.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 信仰によって強くなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.57,0:03:57.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰によって強くなっていたので
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.57,0:04:02.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,この驚くような約束を心から信じました
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.08,0:04:05.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,90歳近くになっていた妻サラから
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.33,0:04:08.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,息子が生まれるという約束です
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.29,0:04:10.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを固く信じました
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.92,0:04:15.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,普通に考えたらとても\N信じられないような約束でしたが
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.92,0:04:19.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,アブラハムは少しも疑いませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.30,0:04:23.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも信仰によって強くなるなら
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.64,0:04:27.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの約束がどんなに\N驚くようなものでも
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.48,0:04:31.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,その全てを全く信じることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.65,0:04:36.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,約束の実現を決して\N疑うことはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.32,0:04:39.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,アブラハムと比較して考えてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.74,0:04:44.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 高齢で体力がなく\N病気のクリスチャンは
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.12,0:04:46.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,弱く見えるかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.58,0:04:50.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 外見だけで\N判断することはできません
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.42,0:04:54.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしその人が信仰によって\N強くなっているなら
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.42,0:04:59.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,アブラハムのように\N本当に強い人といえます
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.05,0:05:04.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,この素晴らしい大会の目的は\N私たちの信仰を強めることです
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.64,0:05:06.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,強い信仰があれば
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.89,0:05:11.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな問題や試練や誘惑に遭うとしても
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.06,0:05:13.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを乗り越えることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.77,0:05:16.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして どんなものも
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.40,0:05:20.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの忠誠を\N打ち砕くことはできません
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.70,0:05:25.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 大会の話や\N素晴らしいドラマによって
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.87,0:05:30.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの信仰はどのように\N強くなったでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.96,0:05:33.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず1日目です
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.38,0:05:38.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,その日の主題は\Nルカ 17:5から取られていました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.34,0:05:41.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,「さらに信仰を与えてください」
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.39,0:05:44.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの使徒たちの謙遜な言葉です
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.35,0:05:48.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒たちはもっと信仰が\N必要であることを認め
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.10,0:05:51.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,「信仰を与えてください」と言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.19,0:05:53.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも同感です
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.40,0:05:55.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,もっと信仰が必要です
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.65,0:05:58.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,「信仰を与えてください」\Nと謙遜に祈ります
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.90,0:06:02.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではエホバは祈りに答え
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.32,0:06:05.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに信仰を与えてくれるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.33,0:06:07.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろんです
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.41,0:06:10.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,1日目には エホバがどんな方法で
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.62,0:06:15.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした祈りに答えてくれるのかを\N学ぶことができました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.17,0:06:17.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,1日目に学んだように
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.51,0:06:22.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが私たちに信仰を与えるために\N使っている本が2冊あります
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.97,0:06:26.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書と創造物です
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.02,0:06:29.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初のシンポジウムでは
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.06,0:06:34.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を学ぶと次のものに信仰を\N持てることが取り上げられました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.65,0:06:38.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の存在 聖書そのもの
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.32,0:06:40.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の道徳基準
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.86,0:06:45.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして私たちに対する神の愛です
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.07,0:06:50.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 神の存在に対する信仰は\Nどのように強まりますか
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.50,0:06:56.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つの点として 聖書の中には\N納得のいく説明があります
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.29,0:06:59.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えばヘブライ 3:4です
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.01,0:07:02.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな聖句でしょうか こうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.80,0:07:07.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,「言うまでもなく 家は全て\N誰かによって造られるのであり
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.01,0:07:11.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,全てのものを造ったのは神です」
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.73,0:07:14.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,美しい家を指さして
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.10,0:07:17.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あの家は設計者がいなくて\Nひとりでに建ったんです」と言っても
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.77,0:07:20.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,信じる人はいないでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.49,0:07:22.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうであれば
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.61,0:07:25.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,星や森や生き物など
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.32,0:07:29.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,自然界に見られる\N美しいものについてはなおのこと
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.66,0:07:34.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,ひとりでにできたなどとは\N考えられないはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.29,0:07:37.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,偶然できたとは考えないでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.79,0:07:40.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,設計が見られるところには
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.09,0:07:43.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ず設計者がいるはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.76,0:07:46.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えで考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.22,0:07:49.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニューヨーク市の完璧な地図を\N天井に描くとします
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.89,0:07:52.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと変わった方法を使います
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.10,0:07:55.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,黒いペンキを缶から天井に\Nただぶちまけるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.81,0:07:58.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを何度も繰り返します
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.90,0:08:02.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,飛び散ったペンキで詳細な\N地図ができるまでやります
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.65,0:08:08.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,全ての道や高速道路やトンネルや\N橋や陸橋や建物もです
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.37,0:08:11.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,それぞれの名前もです
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.33,0:08:14.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,何億回やっても構いません
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.16,0:08:18.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも いくら頑張っても\N完璧な地図などできないでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.17,0:08:21.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここでちょっとユーモアを\N加えさせてください
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.01,0:08:23.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,頑張ってこれを\N1000億年続けたとしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.88,0:08:27.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,なんと ついに地図ができました！
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.39,0:08:30.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも よく見ると\Nニューヨーク市ではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.22,0:08:33.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,小さな田舎町\Nウォーウィックの地図です
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.48,0:08:35.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,これではやり直しです
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.19,0:08:37.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちゃんとニューヨーク市の\N地図ができるまでです
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.98,0:08:39.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご苦労さまです
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.65,0:08:41.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えてみてください
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.73,0:08:44.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間の1つの細胞は
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.36,0:08:46.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニューヨーク市の地図よりも
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.99,0:08:49.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,はるかに複雑で
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.08,0:08:51.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,緻密に設計されています
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.54,0:08:55.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,人体は100兆個ほどの\N細胞でできています
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.37,0:08:58.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,驚くほど複雑な細胞一つ一つが
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.71,0:09:01.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,調和よく機能しているのです
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.80,0:09:04.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,2つ目に 聖書を読むと
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.13,0:09:08.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書そのものに対する信仰が\Nどのように強まりますか
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.64,0:09:12.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つの点として 聖書の\Nアドバイスは全て役に立ち
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.89,0:09:16.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間のアドバイスより\N優れた結果を生み出します
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.39,0:09:20.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,子育てや結婚生活などに\N役立つアドバイスがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.23,0:09:22.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えてみてください
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.32,0:09:27.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間は いつも役立つアドバイスが\Nできるほど賢くはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.03,0:09:33.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間のアドバイスは 時代や\N状況の変化と共に変わります
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.29,0:09:37.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに対し 何千年も前に\N書かれた聖書のアドバイスは
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.17,0:09:39.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,変わることがありません
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.29,0:09:41.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,全てのアドバイスが役に立ちます
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.00,0:09:46.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,高い知恵を持つ方からの\Nものであるに違いありません
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.63,0:09:51.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つ目に 聖書は神の道徳基準への\N信仰をどのように強めますか
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.85,0:09:57.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書は神の基準が何かを説明し\Nそれに従うよう勧めています
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.35,0:10:02.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,従うなら 体や心の健康\Nエホバとの友情を保てます
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.94,0:10:05.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,幸せになれます\N健全な良心を持てます
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.99,0:10:08.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいことずくめです
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.11,0:10:11.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,向こう見ずなことをやってみて\N痛い思いをし
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.28,0:10:14.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこから学ぶという必要はありません
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.66,0:10:19.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,よく 「経験は最高の教師」\Nと言われます
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.08,0:10:21.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは間違いです
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.17,0:10:25.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,あえてつらいことを\N経験する必要はありません
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.09,0:10:27.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,最高の教師はエホバです
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.72,0:10:31.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 19:7にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.09,0:10:35.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバ［は］経験の\N浅い人を賢くする」
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.85,0:10:41.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,4つ目に 聖書は神の愛への\N信仰をどのように強めますか
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.52,0:10:44.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を読むと エホバが初子のイエスを
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.82,0:10:47.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちのために死ぬように\Nされたことが分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.90,0:10:50.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの永遠の命のためです
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.95,0:10:54.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほとんどの人は何かを手放すとき
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.16,0:10:56.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなものを手放しますか
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.33,0:11:00.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,必要のないものや\Nなくても大丈夫なものです
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.29,0:11:03.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバは一番\N大切なものを与えました
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.50,0:11:06.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きな痛みを感じながらです
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.42,0:11:09.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,進化論は 私たちの先祖が
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.43,0:11:12.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,類人猿だと教えています
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.22,0:11:18.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし 私たちのお父さんが\N類人猿だとしたらどう思いますか
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.23,0:11:21.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛されていると感じますか
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.40,0:11:26.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもうれしいことに 私たちの\N本当のお父さんはエホバです
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.19,0:11:28.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛の神です
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.61,0:11:33.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,1日目の午後には 2つ目の\Nシンポジウムがありました
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.95,0:11:37.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,創造物という本をいわば開きました
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.37,0:11:39.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,この本をよく調べると
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.87,0:11:42.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰が強まります
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.42,0:11:47.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず 星について取り上げた\N最初の話を思い出しましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.59,0:11:51.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤ 40:26によると
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.18,0:11:54.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは全ての星を造りました
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.93,0:11:59.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして「全ての星を名で呼」びます
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.48,0:12:01.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと考えてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.85,0:12:04.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,天の川銀河にある星の名前を
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.98,0:12:07.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,1秒に1つずつ挙げていったら
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.90,0:12:10.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれくらい時間がかかると思いますか
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.03,0:12:14.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨセフ パウロ ラケル サラ
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.87,0:12:16.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,科学者たちによると
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.99,0:12:19.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,天の川銀河だけでも
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.45,0:12:23.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐らく4000億個の星が\Nあると言われています
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.17,0:12:27.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,1秒に1個名前を挙げると\N4000億秒かかります
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.17,0:12:29.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,何年になりますか
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.46,0:12:33.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,1万2684年です
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.13,0:12:37.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,アダムが創造されてから今までの\N2倍以上の時間です
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.93,0:12:41.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで終わりではありません\N別の銀河もあります
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.98,0:12:45.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,科学者たちは 宇宙全体には
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.52,0:12:48.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,2兆個の銀河があると考えています
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.44,0:12:53.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,天の川銀河には4000億個の\N星があるということでしたが 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.41,0:12:56.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,その5倍の数の銀河が\Nあることになります
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.83,0:13:00.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,想像しただけでも気が遠くなります
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.87,0:13:05.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもエホバは全ての星を創造し\N制御し 名で呼びます
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.92,0:13:09.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,話の中では エホバにそれができるなら
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.59,0:13:14.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,記念の墓で眠っている\N全ての人のことを記憶し
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.26,0:13:18.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,再創造することができる\Nはずだ と言われました
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.22,0:13:23.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,2つ目の話では 創造物という本の\N海が取り上げられました
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.73,0:13:26.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,海には大きな力があります
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.61,0:13:30.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも海を造った方ははるかに強力です
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.94,0:13:33.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,強力な神エホバは
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.61,0:13:35.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちを今も
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.86,0:13:39.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,大患難の間も必ず守ってくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.08,0:13:44.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つ目の話では \N森が取り上げられました
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.12,0:13:52.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,森林には 自ら再生し回復するという\N素晴らしい能力があることを学びました
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.47,0:13:57.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような森林を創造する\N知恵を持つ神であれば
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.51,0:14:00.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間が地球に与えたダメージを
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.22,0:14:05.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,全て元通りにすることができるはずだ\Nと述べられました
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.65,0:14:10.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,4つ目の話では\N水と風が取り上げられました
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.11,0:14:12.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,話にあった通り エホバは昔
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.94,0:14:15.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,水と風を使いました
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.11,0:14:19.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,特にひょうという形の水を使って\N敵たちを滅ぼし
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.87,0:14:22.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分の民を救出しました
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.70,0:14:26.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハルマゲドンの時も\N水や風を使うでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.08,0:14:31.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,5つ目の話では美しい海の中をのぞき
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.34,0:14:36.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,今地球で生きている一番大きな\N生き物に注目しました
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.22,0:14:38.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,シロナガスクジラです
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.47,0:14:41.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きな体を持つこのクジラは
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.10,0:14:43.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,食欲旺盛です
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.60,0:14:45.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,その話で見たビデオによると
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.98,0:14:49.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,1日に何トンもの餌を食べます
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.23,0:14:51.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもエホバは養っています
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.40,0:14:53.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしそれができるのであれば
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.57,0:14:56.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国をいつも第一にしている私たちを
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.61,0:15:00.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,養い 世話してくれるのでは\Nないでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.24,0:15:05.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバにはその意志と能力がある\Nという信仰が強まりました
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.33,0:15:10.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後の話では 素晴らしい\N人体に注目しました
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.25,0:15:13.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,人体には驚くような能力があります
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.96,0:15:18.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,けがをしても 自己修復能力によって\N回復します
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.26,0:15:21.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,車は傷が付いたりへこんだりしたら
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.72,0:15:25.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,自己修復しますか\Nしません
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.39,0:15:30.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし私たちがあざを作ったり\Nけがをしたり 骨折したりしても
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.48,0:15:32.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,治らなかったらどうなりますか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.02,0:15:37.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,短期間のうちに目も当てられない\N姿になるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.99,0:15:41.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,人体に自己修復能力を組み込んだ神は
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.99,0:15:45.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい世界で全ての病気を治し
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.08,0:15:47.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,老化を逆転させ
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.37,0:15:50.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,病気にかからないように\Nしてくれるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.33,0:15:53.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはそう約束しています
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.21,0:15:55.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つ目のシンポジウムでは
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.21,0:15:59.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰を強める主な本 聖書に\N再び注意を向けました
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.72,0:16:02.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰の強い人たちに注目し
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.76,0:16:07.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らがどのように信仰を\N強めたかを学びました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.10,0:16:10.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らは信仰の欠けた人たちに\N囲まれていましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.60,0:16:13.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰をいっそう強めました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.48,0:16:17.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰を強めるたくさんの\N手本に注目しました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.07,0:16:23.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,アベル エノク ノア モーセ\Nイエスの弟子たちです
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.41,0:16:26.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰の欠けた人ではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.25,0:16:32.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰の強い人に倣いたいという\N願いがいっそう強まりました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.13,0:16:34.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも強い信仰を示せます
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.00,0:16:38.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じお父さん 同じ助け手がいます
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.17,0:16:42.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私たちにも\N聖なる力を与えてくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.89,0:16:46.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,このように 1日目の\N3つのシンポジウムでは
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.39,0:16:51.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが私たちの信仰を強めるために\N使うものに注目しました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.23,0:16:55.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,2冊の本 聖書と創造物です
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.82,0:16:58.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここでドラマについて\Nちょっと考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.95,0:17:02.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに信仰を与えてほしい\Nというダニエルの願いに
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.66,0:17:05.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはどう答えましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.24,0:17:09.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つとして 聖なる書物を与えました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.37,0:17:12.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドラマの中で ダニエルの父親は
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.13,0:17:14.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルに巻物を渡しました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.63,0:17:17.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルはいつもそれを読んでいました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.38,0:17:20.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,その巻物に気付きましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.09,0:17:22.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドラマに出てきた巻物は
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.43,0:17:25.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,今でいう詩編 27編です
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.60,0:17:28.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵たちがダニエルの預言をあざけった時
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.89,0:17:33.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは詩編 27:11, 12を\N思い返しました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.81,0:17:38.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります 「敵対者の手に\N私を渡さないでください
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.61,0:17:41.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,偽りを語る証人が立ち上がり
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.40,0:17:44.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,私を激しく脅してきます」
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.82,0:17:47.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは処刑されそうになった時
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.45,0:17:52.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 27:7-9を\N思い返していました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.50,0:17:54.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.58,0:17:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたは私を助ける方
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.05,0:18:00.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の救いの神 見捨てないでください
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.30,0:18:03.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,放っておかないでください」
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.09,0:18:05.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルはこの聖句を読んで
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.18,0:18:09.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰をとても強められたに\N違いありません
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.10,0:18:12.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが実際にこの聖句を\N思い巡らしたかどうか
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.56,0:18:15.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,はっきりしたことは言えません
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.23,0:18:17.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも聖書からはっきり言えるのは
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.69,0:18:22.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが聖句を読んで\N信仰を強めた ということです
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.07,0:18:27.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご存じのように ダニエルは\N聖書の預言をよく調べました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.53,0:18:30.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 9:2でこう言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.75,0:18:33.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私ダニエルは書物
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.25,0:18:36.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,［聖なる書物］を調べ ⋯⋯\N年数を知った」
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.92,0:18:39.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり エルサレムの荒廃が
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.71,0:18:43.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,「70年」続くということです
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.22,0:18:49.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではエホバは 私たちにもさらに\N信仰を与えてくれますか
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.85,0:18:51.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ず与えてくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.02,0:18:55.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 私たちの信仰を強めるために
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.23,0:18:59.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の預言を与えてくれています
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.90,0:19:04.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に多くの人がダニエル書の\N預言を調べただけで
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.15,0:19:07.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,強い信仰を持つようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.32,0:19:10.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 北の王と南の王の預言が
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.49,0:19:13.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように実現したかを考えると
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.37,0:19:16.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰がとても強まります
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.17,0:19:20.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,この預言について 5月の\Nマンスリープログラムの
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.09,0:19:24.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ケニス･クック兄弟の話を\Nもう一度聞いてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:27.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオをお楽しみください
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.81,0:19:35.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは2人の王が\N敵対することを預言しました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.19,0:19:39.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,「北の王」と「南の王」です
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.11,0:19:42.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように実現してきましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.45,0:19:52.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,1800年代後半 ドイツ帝国が\N北の王になりました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.79,0:19:59.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドイツ政府は 「力と勇気を奮い起こし\N大きな軍隊で南の王を攻め」ました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.21,0:20:03.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界で2番目の規模の\N海軍を持っていました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.43,0:20:08.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 誰が南の王になりましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.05,0:20:13.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,軍事同盟を結んだ英国と米国です
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.27,0:20:19.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,第1次世界大戦中 「非常に\N強大な軍隊で」戦いました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.19,0:20:23.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 北の王を「押し流［し］」\N「打ち負か［し］」ました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.07,0:20:28.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 北の王は活動を\Nやめたわけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.82,0:20:33.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,「聖なる契約に」注意を向け\N「糾弾」を浴びせます
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.29,0:20:37.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 「日ごとの犠牲」\Nを除き去ります
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.75,0:20:41.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の民が伝道を行う自由を制限し
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.63,0:20:46.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,天に行くよう選ばれたクリスチャンと\Nその仲間たちを大勢投獄し
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:49.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,殺すことさえしたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.35,0:20:55.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドイツが第2次世界大戦で敗れた後
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.77,0:20:59.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,ソビエト連邦が北の王になりました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.06,0:21:01.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,北の王は南の王と手を組み
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.90,0:21:05.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,「荒廃をもたらす極めて\N不快なものを据え」ました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.86,0:21:08.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,国際連合です
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.54,0:21:19.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,1900年代の初めから
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.29,0:21:24.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,ソビエト政府は連邦内の\N宗教を排除しようとしました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.17,0:21:32.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうして 「自分の父祖たちの神を\N無視」するという預言が実現しました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.22,0:21:40.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,天の神ではなく\N「要塞の神」をたたえたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.94,0:21:49.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,預言通り 北の王は南の王に軍事力\Nを行使し 「彼と押し合い」ました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.20,0:21:54.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,英米同盟とソビエト連邦は\N覇権争いを続け
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.83,0:21:59.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中の戦争や紛争に関わりました
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.63,0:22:07.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,1991年にソビエト連邦が崩壊した後
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.01,0:22:11.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰が北の王になるのか\Nはっきり分かりませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.55,0:22:17.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,しばらくの間 神の民は\N伝道や崇拝を自由に行えました
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.27,0:22:23.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし近年 ロシアとそれを支持する\N国々は 南の王を押し返しています
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.52,0:22:28.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,どちらの王も相手のサイバー攻撃\Nを非難しています
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.15,0:22:34.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,北の王が攻撃しているのは\N南の王だけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.37,0:22:37.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,預言通り クリスチャンの\N活動領域である
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.95,0:22:41.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,「『美しい地』にも入［って］」います
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.25,0:22:48.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロシア当局は今も真の崇拝への\N攻撃を続けています
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.72,0:22:52.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはそのような迫害を\N予期していました
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.43,0:22:55.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてそれが終わることも知っています
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.91,0:23:20.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの王イエス･キリストは\Nどんな人間の政府よりも強力な方です
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.25,0:23:25.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは間もなく\N北の王と南の王だけでなく
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.54,0:23:28.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,全ての敵を滅ぼします
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.71,0:23:34.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 神を愛する人たちを\N救出するのです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.71,0:24:04.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に励みとなるビデオです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.17,0:24:08.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルの預言が正確に\N実現してきたことを知って
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.63,0:24:11.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの信仰は強まりましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.92,0:24:14.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっとそうだと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.05,0:24:16.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの救出を含め
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.09,0:24:18.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルの預言の残りの部分も
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.64,0:24:21.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ず実現すると確信できます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.89,0:24:25.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,キリストは間もなく神の民を守り
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.06,0:24:30.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,今の邪悪な体制全体を終わらせます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.82,0:24:33.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,この預言や他の預言について
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.40,0:24:36.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,これからも深く学びましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.82,0:24:40.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば 賢くて 強力で
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.95,0:24:47.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛情深いお父さんエホバに対する\N信仰が強まるに違いありません
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.71,0:24:51.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,では2日目のプログラムを\N振り返りましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.26,0:24:54.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題はユダ 3節から取られていました
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.72,0:24:58.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,「信仰のために真剣に戦う」
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.76,0:25:04.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,「信仰のために立派に戦っている\N人たち」というシンポジウムでは
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.69,0:25:07.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,大勢の独身の兄弟姉妹や
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.65,0:25:10.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,夫や妻がまだ信者ではない人たちが
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.78,0:25:14.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰の戦いで勝利を\N収めていることを学びました
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.82,0:25:20.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような兄弟姉妹は 本当に\N素晴らしい努力を払っています
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.24,0:25:24.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマの話では 新しい兄弟姉妹が
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.83,0:25:28.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,これからも信仰を強めるよう\N励まされました
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.75,0:25:33.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマを受けた皆さん全てを\N温かく歓迎します
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.38,0:25:35.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは皆さんを愛しています
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.93,0:25:38.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体も皆さんを愛しています
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.30,0:25:40.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹も皆さんを愛しています
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.97,0:25:47.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,今回皆さんを 固い絆で結ばれた家族に\Nお迎えできたことをうれしく思います
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.52,0:25:52.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,これからも信仰のために\N一緒に戦いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.73,0:25:55.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,2日目午後のシンポジウムでは
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.49,0:25:59.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰を表す方法を\Nさらに学ぶことができました
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.45,0:26:03.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,時間やエネルギーや\N持っているものを使って
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.79,0:26:08.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国の活動に参加し\N他の人を助けることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.67,0:26:13.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,具体的に どんな方法が\N取り上げられたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.21,0:26:17.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 新たな言語を学ぶこと
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.63,0:26:20.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,必要の大きな所に引っ越すこと
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.55,0:26:24.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国福音伝道者のための学校で学ぶこと
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.18,0:26:27.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,建設プロジェクトに参加すること
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.14,0:26:32.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,「取り分け」たものをエホバに\N差し出すことなどです
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.32,0:26:38.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,「信仰のために真剣に戦いましょう！」\Nという話はどうでしたか
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.24,0:26:40.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな戦いについても言えることですが
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.99,0:26:45.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちにも敵がいます
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.33,0:26:48.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 背教者のうそや
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.46,0:26:52.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の反対者の作り話を\N退けなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.75,0:26:55.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らは疑念を生じさせ
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.30,0:26:57.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰を弱めようとしているからです
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.97,0:27:03.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンはネガティブで不正確な情報や\Nうそを巧みに使います
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.81,0:27:05.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから メディアが
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.97,0:27:10.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの組織に関する\Nネガティブで不正確な情報や
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.40,0:27:14.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,うそを使うとしても\N驚くには当たりません
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.36,0:27:17.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうしたメディアは 背教者や聖職者や
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.99,0:27:22.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の反対者に操作されていることが\N少なくありません
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.28,0:27:26.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰は 聖なる力が生み出すものです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.83,0:27:31.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちを強めるために\Nエホバが与えてくださるものです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.54,0:27:33.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに対し疑念は
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.67,0:27:38.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪魔が私たちを\N弱めるために使う道具です
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.92,0:27:42.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンはエバにこのように\N話し掛けました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.34,0:27:45.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたたちは庭園の全ての木の実を
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.18,0:27:49.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,食べてはならない と\N神が言ったのは本当ですか」
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.06,0:27:51.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,「本当ですか」
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.19,0:27:53.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜこんな言い方をしましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.73,0:27:56.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,疑念を抱かせ\N 「信仰を失」わせるためです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.98,0:27:59.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンは成功しました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.07,0:28:04.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも注意しないと信仰を\N失ってしまうかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.24,0:28:10.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 強い信仰があれば 疑念が\N心に入り込むことはないでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.29,0:28:14.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 背教者について\Nもう少し考えてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.09,0:28:18.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,背教者があなたの家のドアを\Nノックしてこう言うとします
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.30,0:28:20.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,「中に入れてくれませんか
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.51,0:28:24.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒に座って私たちの\N考えを聞いてください」
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.10,0:28:27.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう言われたらどうしますか
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.22,0:28:30.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに追い払うのではないでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.64,0:28:33.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,さっさと帰ってもらうはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.48,0:28:38.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,では同じ背教者が別の方法で\N入ってこようとしたらどうしますか
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.36,0:28:41.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,テレビやコンピューターからです
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.74,0:28:44.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん そのようなときにも
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.57,0:28:47.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっぱりと退けたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.41,0:28:51.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ第二 10節にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.08,0:28:53.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,「キリストの教えに従わない人が
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.67,0:28:55.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちの所に来たら
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.92,0:28:58.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,家に迎え入れてはなりません」
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.01,0:29:01.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,玄関に来た場合も
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.05,0:29:04.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,テレビやコンピューターを\N通して来た場合も同じです
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.89,0:29:08.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,残念なことにこう考えて\Nしまった人がいます
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.47,0:29:12.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,「この背教者の言うことを\Nテレビやコンピューターで見たり 
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.35,0:29:14.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,本で読んだりすれば
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.52,0:29:17.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,その間違いがはっきり分かるはずだ
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.27,0:29:19.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰も強まる
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.65,0:29:22.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,伝道で同じようなことを言われた時に
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.49,0:29:26.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,上手に説明できるように\Nなるかもしれない」
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.66,0:29:30.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは本当に愚かな考え方です
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.25,0:29:32.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,こう考えるのと同じです
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.66,0:29:36.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ゴミ箱にある腐った食べ物を食べたら
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.92,0:29:42.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,今後 体に悪い食べ物を\N見分ける助けになるだろう」
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.26,0:29:45.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,いい考えとは言えませんね
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.64,0:29:50.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,背教者の有毒な考えで\N心を養うべきではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.39,0:29:53.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,むしろ聖書を毎日読み
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.06,0:29:57.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰を強め 信仰を守りたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.40,0:30:02.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,では ダニエルは信仰のために\Nどのように戦いましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.78,0:30:09.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つの点として 妥協させようとする\N圧力に抵抗しました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.37,0:30:12.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,王の美食とぶどう酒を勧められた時
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.41,0:30:16.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを断るのは\N簡単ではなかったでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.71,0:30:19.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルはどうしましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.25,0:30:24.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご一緒にダニエル 1章の\N聖句を読んでみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.22,0:30:28.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 1:8です
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.55,0:30:31.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 1:8
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.56,0:30:34.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,「しかしダニエルは
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.52,0:30:41.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,王の美食やぶどう酒で自分を\N汚さないことを心に決めた
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.48,0:30:45.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 自分を汚さずに済むよう
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.11,0:30:48.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,廷臣の長に許可を求めた」
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.03,0:30:51.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは前もって
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.74,0:30:54.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,「心に決め」ていました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.21,0:30:56.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすべきかを決めていたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.96,0:30:59.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして実際にそうしました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.09,0:31:02.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの命令は全て\N自分のためになる ということを
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.01,0:31:06.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,全く確信していたからです
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.30,0:31:13.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも信仰のために\N真剣に戦わなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.27,0:31:15.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしかしたらあなたは今
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.94,0:31:19.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,学校や職場や家庭で
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.02,0:31:22.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,圧力を受けているかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.44,0:31:26.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしそうなら 諦めないでください
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.32,0:31:28.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,決して妥協しないでください
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.70,0:31:31.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルの手本を思い出し
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.16,0:31:33.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰のために戦ってください
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.79,0:31:36.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに従うと心に決めてください
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.71,0:31:40.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに従うのは常に正しいことです
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.75,0:31:45.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに従うなら\N後悔することはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.01,0:31:48.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは別の圧力も受けました
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.72,0:31:50.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,脅しです
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.76,0:31:53.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルの気持ちを\N想像してみてください
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.93,0:31:55.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,今度祈ったら
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.98,0:31:59.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,処刑されるかもしれないのです
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.10,0:32:01.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が助けになりましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.86,0:32:06.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 6章を見て\N答えを探しましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.78,0:32:10.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 6:10です
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.53,0:32:14.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,よろしければご一緒に読んでみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.79,0:32:19.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ダニエルは 法令に\N署名がされたことを知ると
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.21,0:32:22.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに自分の家に入った
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.17,0:32:26.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,屋上の部屋の窓は\Nエルサレムに向かって開かれていた
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.47,0:32:30.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは［次に注目してください］
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.47,0:32:33.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,それまでいつもしていた通り
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.60,0:32:37.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,日に3度ひざまずいて祈り
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.18,0:32:40.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の神を賛美した」
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.73,0:32:43.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは正しいことを
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.23,0:32:45.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ためらわずに行いました
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.69,0:32:48.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,崇拝を続けたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.36,0:32:50.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 6:16には
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.86,0:32:55.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが神に「常に\N仕えてい［た］」とあります
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.12,0:32:58.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ものみの塔」の説明によると
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.25,0:33:03.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,「常に仕えている」と訳されている\N元のアラム語の基本的な意味は
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.42,0:33:05.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,「円を描いて動く」です
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.01,0:33:09.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,継続しているということです
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.26,0:33:12.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは何があっても\N崇拝をやめませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.80,0:33:17.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,円に終わりがないように\Nエホバを崇拝し続けたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.18,0:33:21.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここで 次のビデオをご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.85,0:33:26.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある兄弟が逮捕されそうになります
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.32,0:33:29.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもダニエルの手本を思い巡らし
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.61,0:33:33.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕え続けることができました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.16,0:33:35.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつも通りにです
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.20,0:33:39.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐れを感じるような\N状況でもそうしました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.37,0:33:43.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,首都での混乱はまだ収まっていません
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.84,0:33:50.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,軍が出動し 新政府を支持しない人への\N逮捕・拘束が続いています
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.18,0:33:54.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,今晩は集会に行けるかしら？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.22,0:33:59.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻と娘のことが心配だった
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.94,0:34:06.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,逮捕された長老たちもいる
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.15,0:34:09.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし私が逮捕されたら・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.17,0:34:27.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族はどうなるんだろう？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.86,0:34:49.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,まさか祈らないですよね？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.90,0:34:51.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は窓辺で祈っている
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.15,0:34:56.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,1日3回 毎日だ
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.99,0:35:00.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし 窓辺で祈るのをやめたら
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.08,0:35:04.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなはどう思うだろう？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.83,0:35:07.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私の友だ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.46,0:35:11.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信頼すれば 報いてくださる
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.13,0:35:15.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのようにかは分からない
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.89,0:35:18.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも必ず
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.85,0:35:22.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈ってほしい 私が信仰を貫けるように
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.85,0:35:25.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなが信仰を貫けるように
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.65,0:35:27.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなことがあっても
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.99,0:35:33.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の教えははっきりしている
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.53,0:35:35.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,仲間と集まることをやめてはいけない
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.99,0:35:38.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,少人数になるかもしれないけど
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.74,0:35:40.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒にエホバに祈ろう
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.04,0:35:43.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が起きても耐えられるように
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.88,0:35:49.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,お父さん エホバ⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.34,0:35:51.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,私も逮捕されました
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.14,0:36:06.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしているかな と\Nいつも思っています
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.69,0:36:09.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたのことだから\Nどんな試練に遭っても
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.11,0:36:12.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰を貫くと信じています
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.94,0:36:15.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たち2人も頑張ります
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.24,0:36:19.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,怖かった？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.66,0:36:22.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,怖かったよ
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.91,0:36:27.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもそういうときに\Nエホバは助けてくれる
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.96,0:36:33.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,大丈夫
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.09,0:36:35.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族はエホバが守ってくれる
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.51,0:36:42.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,このビデオに出てきた兄弟と同様
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.64,0:36:45.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも迫害を受けます
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.60,0:36:48.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,テモテ第二 3:12にあるように
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.86,0:36:51.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神への専心を貫き
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.19,0:36:55.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,キリスト･イエスに従って\N生きようとする人は皆
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.28,0:36:57.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じように迫害を受けます」
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.86,0:37:01.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,たぶんとか恐らくとは\N述べられていません
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.12,0:37:05.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,「迫害を受けます」と断言されています
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.41,0:37:10.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオに出てきた兄弟のように\N迫害を受けたら
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.09,0:37:12.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルの手本を思い出し
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.96,0:37:15.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰のために戦いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.47,0:37:23.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに祈ってください\Nエホバはどんな敵たちよりも強いのです
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.22,0:37:27.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ゴリアテと戦った\N若いダビデに倣いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.44,0:37:29.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデは全体像を見ていました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.81,0:37:33.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,巨人ゴリアテを見ていましたが\N全体像を見ていたので
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.94,0:37:37.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,ゴリアテがちっぽけな存在で\Nあることを知っていました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.86,0:37:42.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,全能の神エホバと比べて見ていたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.78,0:37:48.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルもエホバがどれほど\N強力な方かを実感しました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.25,0:37:51.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ライオンの穴に投げ込まれた時です
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.17,0:37:55.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは天使を送って\Nライオンの口をふさぎました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.38,0:37:59.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えてみてください ライオンは\N空腹だったに違いありません
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.38,0:38:02.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,少し後に投げ込まれた人たちは
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.22,0:38:05.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,穴の底に落ちる前に\N食べられてしまったからです
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.85,0:38:11.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,空腹なライオンにとって ダニエルは\Nおいしそうなごちそうに見えたでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.06,0:38:13.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもライオンは どんなに頑張っても
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.94,0:38:16.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルに対して口を開けて
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.61,0:38:20.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,襲い掛かることはできませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.28,0:38:23.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは別の手本も示しています
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.28,0:38:26.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,高齢で体力が弱ってからも
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.37,0:38:29.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,前向きな見方を保ちました
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.21,0:38:31.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが100歳近くの時
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.29,0:38:34.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くのユダヤ人は懐かしい\N故国ユダに戻りました
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.75,0:38:39.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもダニエルは一緒に行けませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.13,0:38:43.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 前向きな見方を持つ上で\N何が助けになりましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.30,0:38:46.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご一緒にダニエル 10章を\N見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.52,0:38:49.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が助けになったでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.48,0:38:51.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 10:18からです
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.94,0:38:54.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルはこう言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.15,0:38:59.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,「人のような姿の者は再び私に触れて\N力づけてくれた
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.78,0:39:04.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてこう言った 『大切な人よ\N恐れることはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.74,0:39:06.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたに平和がありますように
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.04,0:39:10.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,勇気を出し 強くありなさい』
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.75,0:39:15.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼が話しているうちに\N私は力づけられ こう言った
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.96,0:39:21.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,『どうぞお話しください あなたは\N私を力づけてくださいました』」
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.34,0:39:23.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは天使を通して
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.51,0:39:25.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが大切な人で
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.93,0:39:30.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分にとって非常に有用な\N存在であることを伝えました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.98,0:39:34.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルはとても力づけられました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.06,0:39:38.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後エホバはダニエルに\N北の王と南の王に関する
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.23,0:39:41.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,わくわくするような預言を書かせました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.11,0:39:43.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちのためにです
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.20,0:39:47.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,高齢で体力が弱っていましたが\Nこの大切な人は
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.49,0:39:51.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバにとって有用な存在でした
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.75,0:39:55.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうぞ次のビデオをご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.54,0:39:59.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある高齢の兄弟は\N少しがっかりしていましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.88,0:40:04.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,天使に励まされた\Nダニエルのことを思い返します
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.27,0:40:15.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,時が過ぎるのは早いものです
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.57,0:40:21.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓奉仕
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.57,0:40:25.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,外国語での奉仕
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.66,0:40:28.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,巡回奉仕
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.87,0:40:35.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,少し前までは 私が高齢の人たちを\N励ましていました
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.29,0:40:39.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの頃が本当に懐かしい
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.42,0:40:44.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では私が世話を受けている
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.22,0:40:53.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,もうできることが何もないように\N感じることがある
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.32,0:41:01.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,大切な人ダニエル
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.49,0:41:05.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は遣わされてきました
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.49,0:41:10.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐れることはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.41,0:41:15.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが謙遜になろうと\N心に決めた最初の日から
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.25,0:41:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈りは聞かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.04,0:41:20.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう力が出ません
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.42,0:41:23.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,息をするのも大変です
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.38,0:41:27.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,大切な人ダニエル \N恐れることはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.39,0:41:30.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,大丈夫です
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.72,0:41:32.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,勇気を出してください
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.10,0:41:40.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,待ち続ける人は幸せです！
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.32,0:41:42.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後まで進んでいきなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.69,0:41:45.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは休みますが 日々の終わりに
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.66,0:41:49.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,報いを受けるために立ち上がります
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.16,0:41:53.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんにちは 調子はどうですか
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.83,0:41:57.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと時間ある？\N見せたいものがあるんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.83,0:41:59.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいですよ
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.89,0:42:12.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私のことを\N大切に思っておられる
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.77,0:42:16.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,できることはまだまだある
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.65,0:42:23.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に感動的なビデオでした
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.44,0:42:26.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは健康上の問題のために
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.28,0:42:29.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,できることが限られていますか
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.12,0:42:32.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしそうなら ダニエルの\N手本を思い出し
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.91,0:42:35.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバから力を得ましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.58,0:42:38.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが以前に行ったことを
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.67,0:42:42.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは今でも大切に思っています
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.25,0:42:44.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,決して忘れたりはされません
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.80,0:42:47.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてあなたが今していることは
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.84,0:42:53.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえ小さくても エホバにとって\Nとても大切です
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.06,0:42:55.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんにお勧めします
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.27,0:42:59.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,若くても高齢でも\Nダニエルに倣ってください
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.15,0:43:04.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰のために真剣に戦い続けてください
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.57,0:43:07.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,では3日目のプログラムを\N振り返りましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.74,0:43:12.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ 21:21に基づく主題でした
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.28,0:43:16.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,「信仰を持[つ]なら ⋯⋯\Nそうなります」
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.91,0:43:21.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,午前には 信仰を強める\Nシンポジウムを楽しみました
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.63,0:43:25.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,「強い信仰を持つ女性から\N学ぶ」という主題です
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.76,0:43:29.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,8部から成るこのシンポジウムに\N出てきた女性たちは
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.22,0:43:31.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,強い信仰を示して
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.55,0:43:35.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,山のような問題を\N乗り越えることができました
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.60,0:43:41.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,サラは 快適な生活を後にして\N遊牧生活をしました
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.44,0:43:45.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして何年も子供ができませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.73,0:43:50.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラハブは命を懸けて\N思い切った行動を取りました
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.36,0:43:55.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,イスラエルの偵察者たちを守り\N神の民の側に付いたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.37,0:44:00.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,またその後 不道徳な\N生き方をやめました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.75,0:44:03.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハンナは何年も子供ができず
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.25,0:44:08.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペニンナから嫌がらせを受けましたが\Nエホバに仕え続けました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.59,0:44:10.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,イスラエルの少女は
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.63,0:44:14.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,シリアの略奪者たちによって\N無理やり家族から引き離され
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.51,0:44:16.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,捕らわれの身になりました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.72,0:44:21.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでも エホバについて\N恐れることなく
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.06,0:44:23.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の人に伝え続けました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.81,0:44:27.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,マリアは難しい務めを受け入れました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.94,0:44:32.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の子を産み 養い\N育て上げるという務めです
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.03,0:44:38.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,フェニキア人の女性は邪悪な天使に\N取りつかれた娘を治してほしいと
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.20,0:44:42.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスに大胆に\N粘り強くお願いしました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.21,0:44:45.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,願い通り癒やされました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.13,0:44:49.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,マルタは兄弟を亡くして\N悲しみに暮れていましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.51,0:44:55.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが死者を復活させることが\Nできると信じていました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.64,0:44:59.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後の話では 現代の\N2人の例に注目しました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.43,0:45:02.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,石井姉妹とトーム姉妹です
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.23,0:45:05.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人とも エホバの証人だという理由で
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.02,0:45:08.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,何年も拘禁されました
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.15,0:45:13.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでも 信仰を捨てることを\Nきっぱり拒みました
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.20,0:45:16.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,石井姉妹もトーム姉妹も
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.41,0:45:19.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,山のような問題にぶつかりました
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.62,0:45:23.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもエホバは2人の信仰に報いました
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.88,0:45:28.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人はエホバが良いことを\Nしてくれると信じていました
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.46,0:45:33.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして実際にエホバから祝福されました
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.22,0:45:35.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,強い信仰を保つなら
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.35,0:45:39.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがどんなことをしてくれると\N期待できますか
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.39,0:45:44.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,間もなく起きると予告されている事柄を\N幾つか考えてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.52,0:45:47.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば ダニエル 2章に出てくる
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.07,0:45:53.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネブカドネザルの像の夢の\N最後の部分が実現します
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.20,0:45:57.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,像の上から4つの部分で表される
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.53,0:46:02.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,4つの強国は すでに現れ\N過ぎ去りました
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.54,0:46:04.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,予告通りにです
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.63,0:46:07.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,今 世界に大きな影響を与えているのは
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.96,0:46:13.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,鉄と粘土でできた足で\N表されている英米です
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.38,0:46:16.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは この最後の強国が
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.60,0:46:19.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,鉄と粘土のように分裂した様子を
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.02,0:46:22.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまで以上に見ています
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.39,0:46:27.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,粘土が混ざった鉄が\N鉄の塊より弱いのと同じように
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.52,0:46:32.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,英米は鉄のような\Nローマ帝国より弱いと言えます
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.11,0:46:36.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ローマ帝国は 英米の\N母体となった帝国です
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.28,0:46:39.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,英米は 粘土のようなものによって
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.12,0:46:42.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,鉄のような強さを\N発揮することができません
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.87,0:46:47.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 暴動によって権利を\N主張する人たちがいます
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.38,0:46:51.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,公民権運動や独立運動を\N行う人たちもいます
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.80,0:46:56.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,このような人たちが足の粘土の部分です
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.51,0:46:59.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 2:42にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.93,0:47:06.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,「この王国には強い部分と\Nもろい部分があることになります」
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.19,0:47:11.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,今そのことは かつてないほど\N明らかになっています
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.07,0:47:16.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,この最後の強国は弱体化しているものの
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.99,0:47:19.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのまま力を失って
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.62,0:47:22.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,自滅するわけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.16,0:47:24.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 2章を開いて
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.66,0:47:27.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうなるか見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.29,0:47:31.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 2:44からです
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.13,0:47:33.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,「この王たちの時代に
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.46,0:47:38.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,天の神は決して滅ぼされることのない\N王国を建てます
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.55,0:47:42.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,その王国はほかのどんな民にも\N渡されません
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.85,0:47:47.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらの王国を全て打ち砕いて終わらせ
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.56,0:47:51.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,その王国だけが永遠に存続します
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.61,0:47:55.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,山から1つの石が人手によらずに
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.03,0:47:59.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,［つまりエホバの手によって］\N切り出され
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.66,0:48:03.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,鉄 銅 粘土 銀 金を打ち砕いたのを
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.50,0:48:06.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたがご覧になった通りです
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.92,0:48:11.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,偉大な神が 将来起きる事柄を\N王に知らせました
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.59,0:48:13.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,この夢は真実であり
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.01,0:48:17.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,解き明かしも確かです」
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.26,0:48:20.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,石で表される神の王国は
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.60,0:48:24.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハルマゲドンで人間の政府を\N打ち砕きます
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.81,0:48:28.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,全ての政府を滅ぼすのです
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.77,0:48:34.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,興味深いことに\Nダニエル 2:34によると
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.11,0:48:37.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,「石［つまり神の王国］が
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.07,0:48:39.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,［人間の政府を表す］像の
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.78,0:48:43.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,鉄と粘土でできた足の所を打」ちます
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.41,0:48:45.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が分かりますか
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.45,0:48:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハルマゲドンは 人間が支配する\N最後の強国である
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.04,0:48:56.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,英米がまだ存続している間に\N来る ということです
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.17,0:49:02.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはダニエルと同じように\N次のことを確信しています
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.68,0:49:04.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,45節の最後です
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.77,0:49:08.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,「この夢は真実であり\N解き明かしも確かです」
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.81,0:49:10.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,疑問の余地はありません
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.02,0:49:14.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の王国は英米が存続している間に
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.78,0:49:20.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハルマゲドンで人間の全ての\N政府を滅ぼすのです
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.36,0:49:25.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,像の夢の最後の部分が\N間もなく実現するのと同じように
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.70,0:49:32.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 7章の幻の最後の部分も\N間もなく実現します
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.29,0:49:34.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが見たこの幻には
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.80,0:49:37.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,獣が4匹出てきます
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.13,0:49:42.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらの獣はかつて存在した\N4つの強国を表しています
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.22,0:49:45.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,この獣という表現はぴったりです
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.47,0:49:48.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,支配の仕方が穏やかでなく
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.27,0:49:51.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,獣のように荒々しいからです
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.94,0:49:54.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,この4つの強国とは
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.23,0:49:57.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロン メディア･ペルシャ\Nギリシャ ローマです
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.78,0:50:00.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここに出てくる4つの国は
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.57,0:50:03.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,像の上から4つの部分が\N表す国と同じです
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.95,0:50:08.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,先ほど考えたダニエル 2章の像です
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.33,0:50:10.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは7:8で
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.67,0:50:16.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,ローマを表す4匹目の獣の頭から\N生えてきた角に注意を向けています
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.92,0:50:19.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,その角には目があり
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.55,0:50:24.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,口があり 高慢に語ります
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.22,0:50:30.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,この高慢な角は何を表していますか\N英米を表しています
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.60,0:50:34.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,繰り返しますが 最後の強国です
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.73,0:50:38.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,次にどうなることが予告されていますか
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.32,0:50:41.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 7章を見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.36,0:50:43.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,次に起きる事柄です
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.62,0:50:49.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 7:26から\N読んでみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.41,0:50:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「しかし 法廷が開廷し
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.04,0:50:57.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼の統治権［つまり高慢な角の\N統治権］を取り去りました
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.13,0:51:01.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼を根絶やしにし\N完全に滅ぼすためです
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.38,0:51:07.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国と 統治権と 天の下の\N全ての王国の栄光は
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.64,0:51:11.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,至上者の聖なる者たちに与えられました
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.89,0:51:16.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らの王国は永遠に存続し
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.15,0:51:22.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,全ての国の人々は\N彼らに仕え 従います」
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.49,0:51:26.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,この高慢な角は統治権を取り去られ
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.62,0:51:28.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,根絶やしにされ 滅ぼされ
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.70,0:51:32.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,代わりに神の王国が統治します
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.54,0:51:35.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,この幻で描写されている通り
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.67,0:51:41.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の王国は最後の強国である\N英米が存続している間に
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.92,0:51:45.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間の全ての政府を滅ぼします
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.39,0:51:49.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして地球全体を治めるようになります
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.60,0:51:52.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,胸の躍るような出来事です
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.39,0:51:56.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうしたことが間もなく生じるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.94,0:52:02.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えてみてください この預言は\N今まで全て実現してきました
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.40,0:52:05.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから この預言の最後の部分も
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.82,0:52:11.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ず実現すると\N100パーセント確信できます
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.12,0:52:13.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日は取り上げる時間が\Nありませんでしたが 
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.62,0:52:17.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル書にはほかにも\Nたくさんの預言があり
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.13,0:52:20.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,詳細な点に至るまで実現してきました
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.71,0:52:24.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,これほど多くの預言が\N実現しているということは
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.63,0:52:26.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,この体制の終わりが
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.01,0:52:31.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に 非常に近い証拠です
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.31,0:52:38.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,間もなく私たちはダニエル 12:1の\N預言の実現を目撃することでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.19,0:52:43.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,その預言によると 「偉大な長\Nミカエルが行動を起こします」
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.40,0:52:46.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,「そして［大きな］苦難の時が来ます」
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.78,0:52:50.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 神の民は「逃れます」
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.16,0:52:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「書に記されている人は\N皆 逃れ」るのです
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.08,0:52:57.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,この話の最初の方で見たビデオでは
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.00,0:53:01.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカエルつまり栄光を受けた\Nイエス･キリストが
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.88,0:53:05.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,天使と共に来て 神の民を救出し
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.68,0:53:10.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,今の邪悪な体制を滅ぼす様子が\N描かれていました
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.47,0:53:13.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオをよく見ると分かりますが
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.27,0:53:17.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵たちは銃を空に向けて
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.35,0:53:21.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカエルを撃とうとしていました
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.98,0:53:24.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,無駄な抵抗です
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.36,0:53:27.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間が造った最も強力な武器も
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.49,0:53:29.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカエルの力に比べれば
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.03,0:53:32.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,しけた花火のようなものです
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.66,0:53:34.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオに出てきたミカエルは
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.83,0:53:37.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,防御用の装備を\N身に着けていませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.96,0:53:40.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,胸当ても盾もありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.88,0:53:42.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,必要ないのです
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.92,0:53:45.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,持っていたのは剣だけです
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.01,0:53:48.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,攻撃用の武器です
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.18,0:53:52.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,挿絵によってはイエスが\N弓と矢を持っています
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.64,0:53:56.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,やはり攻撃用の武器しか持っていません
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.14,0:54:00.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもイエスが攻撃に使う武器は強力です
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.48,0:54:04.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,その武器にはすさまじい威力があります
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.48,0:54:07.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから エホバの民を救出し
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.61,0:54:13.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンの邪悪な体制全体を\N一掃するのは簡単なことです
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.24,0:54:21.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハルマゲドンの後 キリスト･イエスの\N輝かしい千年統治が始まります
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.88,0:54:24.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,その素晴らしい時の間
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.84,0:54:30.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル書の最後の節が実現します
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.05,0:54:37.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んでみましょう\Nダニエル書の最後の節 12:13です
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.81,0:54:40.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルに語られた言葉です
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.40,0:54:44.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたは最後まで進んでいきなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.53,0:54:46.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは休みますが
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.90,0:54:52.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,日々の終わりに 報いを\N受けるために立ち上がります」
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.41,0:54:55.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは生涯の最後まで
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.24,0:54:57.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに忠実に仕えました
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.75,0:54:59.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,「最後まで進ん［だ］」のです
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.96,0:55:02.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,今は死んで休んでいますが
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.75,0:55:06.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,間もなく復活して「立ち上がります」
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.67,0:55:10.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,キリストの千年統治の間\N 「報い」を受けます
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.43,0:55:13.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい世界での報いです
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.43,0:55:16.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが天使を通して約束したことに
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.56,0:55:19.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは信仰を持ちましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.85,0:55:22.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん 持ちました
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.31,0:55:25.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,すでに何十年も信仰を示していました
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.61,0:55:28.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,美食を勧められても食べませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.49,0:55:31.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分を汚したくなかったからです
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.61,0:55:33.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎日欠かさず祈りました
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.91,0:55:37.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,処刑されると脅されてもそうしました
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.58,0:55:42.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書をよく学び 信仰を強め続けました
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.50,0:55:46.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから ダニエルはエホバが\N天使を通して約束したことを
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.88,0:55:49.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,心から信じたに違いありません
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.26,0:55:55.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,復活して立ち上がり 新しい世界で\N報いを受けるという約束です
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.35,0:55:57.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,では どうでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.43,0:56:02.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはどうすれば\Nダニエルのように信仰を保てますか
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.40,0:56:04.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰を弱めないようにするため
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.73,0:56:09.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの絆を大切にし\N道徳的な清さを保ちましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.82,0:56:12.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつも祈ってください
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.20,0:56:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが必ず聞いてくれる\Nという確信を抱きましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.04,0:56:19.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書をよく学ぶことによって
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.41,0:56:22.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの言葉を注意深く聞いてください
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.96,0:56:25.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私たちに\N報いたいと願っています
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.96,0:56:29.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことを信じてほしいと思っています
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.13,0:56:31.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘブライ 11:6にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.93,0:56:36.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神に近づく人は\N神が存在し［本当にいて］
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.22,0:56:38.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,熱心に仕えようと努める人たちに
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.97,0:56:44.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,報いてくださる ということを\N信じなければなりません」
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.23,0:56:48.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオに出てきた2人の\N兄弟のことを思い出してください
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.40,0:56:52.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,クリスチャンである父親と\N病気の兄弟です
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.49,0:56:55.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,父親は結局逮捕されました
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.91,0:56:59.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,病気の兄弟は\N回復したわけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.45,0:57:02.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,では2人の信仰は無駄でしたか
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.37,0:57:05.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのようなことは決してありません
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.38,0:57:07.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは2人に報いますか
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.00,0:57:10.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん 報います
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.92,0:57:14.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが同じような\N状況に置かれているなら
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.18,0:57:16.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはあなたに報いますか
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.55,0:57:19.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん 報います
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.06,0:57:22.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のビデオをご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.81,0:57:25.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,大会の最後にみんなで歌う
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.81,0:57:28.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリジナルソングの\Nミュージックビデオです
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.32,0:57:31.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうぞお楽しみください
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.76,0:58:04.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,炎のように迫る敵たち
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.48,0:58:08.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐れはしない
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.44,0:58:17.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつもそばにエホバがいるから
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.95,0:58:24.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの助けを信じ
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.79,0:58:31.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたから離れない
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.01,0:58:39.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,力もらって強くなろう
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.68,0:58:45.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,進みつづけていこう
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.35,0:58:49.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたと
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.33,0:59:13.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは友を忘れることなく
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.13,0:59:26.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,また再び目覚めさせる 新しい世界で
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.48,0:59:33.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの助けを信じ
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.32,0:59:40.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたから離れない
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.62,0:59:48.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,力もらって強くなろう
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.29,0:59:53.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,進みつづけていこう
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.92,0:59:58.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたと
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.22,1:00:04.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,確かな希望がある
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.97,1:00:11.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,試練の向こうに
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.31,1:00:18.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,揺るがず立ちつづけていく
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.78,1:00:28.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰抱いて
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.37,1:00:41.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,未来が見える もう目の前に
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.76,1:00:49.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,守り抜く この信仰
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.19,1:00:55.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの勝利まで
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.61,1:01:02.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの助けを信じ
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.49,1:01:09.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたから離れない
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.75,1:01:17.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,力もらって強くなろう
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.46,1:01:23.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,進みつづけていこう
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.51,1:01:32.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,未来へ
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.40,1:01:48.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.50,1:01:55.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に心を揺さぶられるビデオでした
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.71,1:02:02.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,大会の最後に 皆さんと一緒に\Nこの歌を歌えるのがとても楽しみです
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.68,1:02:06.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛する兄弟姉妹 子供たち
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.81,1:02:09.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書に関心を持つ皆さん 
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.47,1:02:16.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは今強力な敵と戦っています
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.23,1:02:21.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つは私たち自身の\N中にいる強力な敵です
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.65,1:02:23.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,受け継いだ罪です
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.70,1:02:29.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,この敵は 正しいことをしたいという\N私たちの願いを攻撃します
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.75,1:02:33.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,2つ目に 非常に強力な敵である
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.37,1:02:36.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンと邪悪な天使たちがいます
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.67,1:02:40.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンは聖書で むさぼり食うライオン
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.38,1:02:44.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうかつな蛇 どう猛な竜
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.43,1:02:48.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,鳥をわなで捕る者などと呼ばれる\N危険な存在です
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.97,1:02:53.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,エフェソス 6:12にある通り\N 「私たちは戦っている
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.27,1:02:56.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,［直訳によると 格闘をして］\Nいるからです⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.61,1:03:01.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,天にいる邪悪な天使の\N勢力と戦っています」
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.07,1:03:04.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,出版物の中で説明されている通り
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.20,1:03:06.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,邪悪で強力な天使が
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.87,1:03:10.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,目に見えない領域に非常に大勢いて
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.00,1:03:15.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちに戦いを仕掛けています
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.12,1:03:19.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つ目は 周囲の邪悪な世界です
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.71,1:03:22.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちに圧力をかけて
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.38,1:03:26.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に喜ばれないことをさせようとします
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.80,1:03:28.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,人口比で見ると
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.97,1:03:34.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの民の数は そうではない\N人たちと比べて非常に少数です
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.48,1:03:37.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,約900人に1人です
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.98,1:03:42.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,この3つの敵は非常に強力ですが
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.53,1:03:48.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,宇宙で最も強力な力である\N聖なる力が生み出す信仰があれば 
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.37,1:03:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たち一人一人はますます強くなり
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.04,1:03:58.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,この3つの敵全てに\N立ち向かうことができます
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.54,1:04:04.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,間もなく もう1つの強力な敵が\N私たちを攻撃します
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.34,1:04:06.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,この恐ろしい敵は
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.55,1:04:12.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,エゼキエル 38章でゴグと\N呼ばれている諸国家の連合体です
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.06,1:04:16.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,エゼキエル 38章によると\Nゴグは「大勢いて
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.85,1:04:18.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,大軍を成して」います
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.02,1:04:21.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,「土地を覆う雲のように」
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.52,1:04:25.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の民に攻撃を仕掛けます
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.15,1:04:28.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に恐ろしい状況になることでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.74,1:04:32.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも愛する兄弟姉妹 信仰があれば
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.49,1:04:35.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,ゴグより強くなることができます
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.71,1:04:37.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんはますます強くなります
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.96,1:04:42.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてエホバはハルマゲドンで\N奇跡的に救出してくれます
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.46,1:04:45.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハルマゲドンは救出作戦です
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.59,1:04:47.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは行動を起こし
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.63,1:04:52.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の民を攻撃するゴグを\N「滅亡のほうき」で一掃します
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.85,1:04:56.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,ゴグは完全にいなくなります
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.48,1:05:00.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,昔 神の民は信仰によって
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.61,1:05:05.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に大きな問題を\N乗り越えることができました
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.11,1:05:07.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも信仰があれば
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.82,1:05:10.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,問題を乗り越えられます
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.28,1:05:12.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,今も昔も同じです
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.95,1:05:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルなど神に仕えた人たちが
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.04,1:05:19.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,強くなれたのは
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.88,1:05:24.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分に力があったからではなく\N信仰があったからです
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.88,1:05:27.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,では愛する兄弟姉妹
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.93,1:05:29.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,子供たち
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.01,1:05:32.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書に関心を持つ皆さん
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.18,1:05:34.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰を祈り求めてください
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.02,1:05:38.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰のために真剣に戦いましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.39,1:05:41.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のことを固く信じてください
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.15,1:05:46.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰があれば 信仰を保てば\N信仰によって歩めば
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.49,1:05:48.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは必ず
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.57,1:05:54.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの約束が全て実現するのを\N見ることができるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.06,1:05:59.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがとうございました
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.14,1:06:04.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,レット兄弟の話と この地区大会\N全体によって信仰が強められ
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.27,1:06:07.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,将来に備えることができました
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.32,1:06:12.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんにうれしいお知らせがあります
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.24,1:06:17.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ダニエル 信仰を貫いた人」という\Nドラマの第1部と第2部を
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.70,1:06:21.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,jw.orgと\NJW Library®アプリで
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.29,1:06:24.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダウンロードすることができます
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.75,1:06:30.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会を通して\N世界の状況が厳しい中でも
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.92,1:06:34.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが強い信仰を\N保つために必要なものを
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.30,1:06:39.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとイエスが豊かに与えて\Nくださることを確信できました
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.98,1:06:43.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に感謝できるのではないでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.06,1:06:46.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここで 統治体の兄弟たちと
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.69,1:06:53.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中で熱心に働いているベテル家族や\N翻訳事務所の兄弟姉妹を代表して
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.74,1:06:59.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,2021地区大会を視聴して\Nくださったことに感謝いたします
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.16,1:07:02.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは皆さんを愛しており
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.50,1:07:08.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんが愛や信仰や希望を\N強く保つことを願っています
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.42,1:07:10.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の世界本部から
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.63,1:07:14.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,JW Broadcasting®が\Nお送りしてきました
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.30,1:07:22.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後に 信仰を持って歩み続ける\N決意を表す歌を歌いましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.48,1:07:27.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,「信仰を抱いて」と題する\Nオリジナルソングを歌いたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.02,1:07:31.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,結びの話の中で聞いた歌です
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.61,1:07:37.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌の後 それぞれの場所で\N結びの祈りを捧げてください
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.32,1:07:42.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,では ものみの塔コーラス隊と\N一緒に大きな声で歌いましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.62,1:07:45.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,「信仰を抱いて」
